\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Mrs Davies was married in 1911 and born in 1887.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You were born at Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, Chip Hill, Oakworth. Chip Hill Oakworth. Bockthorn - Chip Hill, Bockthorn, they call it Chip Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could you tell me how many years you lived in the house where you were born, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh well I were born at - I don't - oh I don't remember being born all - don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't remember. It'd be at Oakworth. I was born at Oakworth, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where's the first house you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In Mill Lane, we - I can remember living in Mill Lane in Oakworth. You know that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't know how long we lived there. Oh don't know how long we lived there. No. It was a few - few years that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you go to live after Mill Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Then - that
 other house we were living besides Mill Lane, we lived - I can't remember. Lived in two houses in Mill Lane. I don't remember where - where we lived after Mill Lane, only I was born in this house at Chip Hill but beyond that I don't know anything about -
 only know what we mother - well you can tell, I'm so - so long since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your early memories are of mill Lane are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 
There was - there was in Mill Lane, I - I must have gone to - to start at the Mill there because I worked at Armitage's at the bottom of Mill Lane you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you must have lived around Mill Lane until you were about eleven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Around - in Oakworth - yes, it - well think that we - I came down to Holy Cross school from Oakworth. I lived at Oakworth then, to pass t
his exam you see and then when I passed this exam it was only standard two. We passed the exam and then we could go to - to work and work full time you see. So I can't tell you anything about that, I can't remember it. Those incidents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Most of the time you were in Oakworth you lived in Mill Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were about twelve you moved from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207  Oakworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you move to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We moved to Park Grove down Lawkholme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That was when you were about twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it's be - I should say - it'd be round about twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Down Lawkholme Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you live there until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. Well - then we went from Park Grove into Mare Street, number thirty, I can remember this quite well, number th
irty Nares Street. Nares - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Nares}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 Street. It's up Highfield Lane. Yes, we went to live up there in Nares Street. Me father died there you see. Me father died when we lived in Nares Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long did you stay there, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't know how long we stayed in Nares Street. You see, I can't remember years. No. Don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you got married where were you living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In Lawkholme. In Marlborough Street, I was married from Marlborough Street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you were married in 1911 weren't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you moved around quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh, moved around ever such a lot. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You had three brothers and three sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember how they were spaced out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh, two years between us all
 about, two years that and a month at either side of the two years you know. The - always - how was they always used to have their children didn't they, every two years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you come in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I think I was about the - the third.
 I had three - two sisters older than me and one sister younger and two brothers younger so I'd be about the fourth wouldn't I. Yes. About the fourth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd be about half way wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I'd be about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Three older and three younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, yes. I would be about half way. They all died you see but for the one brother and I had him down Saturday. Just one brother - just - and he's eighty. He's eighty-one twenty - twentieth of November. He's younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
When I was born? No I can't remember, can't remember a right lot about - father taking me to Sunday school. He was chairman at the Sunday school were me father. A right good living man. And - he used to take me to 
Sunday school. Oh we were at Coppey Row, do you know Coppey Row? Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you move there after Mill Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we lived there before, I were only ever such a toddler. I can remember a young man that lived next door to us, ever so well, yes. Be
tty Wright they called her, she were right buxom - the mother was, a right buxom woman, you know, and a happy face. They used to be like that didn't they. She was a lovely -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you lived at Coppey Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And we lived at Coppey Lane, that's at bo
ttom of Lowerbank and we used to go to Slack lane - Slack Lane Chapel. Up Lowerbank and on a - I don't know what they call it - and then down Kewer Hill and then to Slack Lane Chapel. And we used to take our dinner. Yes. Yes, we used to take our - our din
n
er to Slack Lane and they had a oven there and a kitchen and used to - they used to put this oven on, it'd be coal or something to heat the place perhaps and we used to put our bit of dinner into this one and warm it and then stay to the afternoon service
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 To save you walking home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh we couldn't walk home. Too far. We had to take - I was - I was Slack Lane not so long ago and I was a telling a man there and I said, oh I could tell you - my mother and father was the first to be married at Slack L
ane and they give hem a - a photograph of the chapel you know, for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Had the chapel just been erected then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, well I don't know but they was the first to be married at this chapel at Slack Lane. I - I know, yes, I've a cousin at Queensbury th
at goes out speaking at women's meetings and she had speak at this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 meeting at Slack Lane so she wrote and told me, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 said}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 would you like to come with me. I says, I would I'd love it. So I went to Oakworth. Went on the bus and we went Slack Lane. So that's - I can remember that bit of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your father talking about where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. He came from Ely. Yes. He was - he was baptised in a river at Ely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Is that spelt Healey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, Ely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In Norfolk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I don't know - I know I've heard him talk about it. That's where he came from. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know what his occupation was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know what he did but he was a weaver that was all I know, when - when - after we were - after mother were mar
ried to him. I don't know what he did before you see, but - when he died he was a weaver.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you ever remember him being anything else, other than being a weaver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't. Don't remember him - I can't remember a lot - I can remember seeing 
him, I know - I know of him and I can remember this little bit of him - passing in my - when my youth you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't ever remember him being out of work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he was always out of work, oh - that - it was in them days you know. Used t
o be - go from one place to another you see. To work. Well he used to be out of work quite a - we had a struggle you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know how old your mother would be when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't now when I were born, I know she was eighty-four when I - she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know when she died - when our Elsie went to school, oh I don't - can't think when - I can't think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You haven't her birth certificate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I haven't me mother's. I have me own - my own birth certificate but not mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know where she came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - can't think what - I think I've heard her tell - her grandmother - her mother, I can remember her but I - I can't remember - I can't remember where they lived. No I can't.
 She lived with us at Oakworth, what I can remember about her, she lived with us you see. They used to do in them days didn't they, all live together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Had she any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 My mother? She were a washerwomen that were all. She 
used to wash for - oh this is after - I don't know what she did before I - before she were married. I don't know anything about her then. But when I was ever such a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 girl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  she used to wash for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Burwen's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  at Oakworth, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - you wouldn't know them. Burwens, they
 lived up top of Brigg - top of the Brigg, they call it Brigg. We - you see, we used to call it different to what you call it. It was right big houses at - right at the top of - was it up Brigg, no - no, no, it weren't up Brigg. She did wash for Harris's 
at top of the - she used to do washing, that were how they got their living in them days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she used to go out to wash at their houses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they used to bring it home because they were - we were all babies you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So it was a sort of part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Washing, yes, she used to wash, yes she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Which is the house you remember best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well in Mill Lane. Before I left school? In Mill Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh my goodness, no, only about two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And two downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. And there were a kitchen then another room downstairs yes, a kitchen and a room downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And your grandma lived with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there anyone else living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 M
e Uncle, me Uncle Ben they call him, that's me - the lady that I tell that lives on Goodley, Auntie Emma, it were her husband, she married him, Uncle Ben and he lived with us 'cos he - he didn't get married 'til }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 late}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  in life. And he lived with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That would be your mother's brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. My mother's brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you had all you seven children living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your mother, father, grandma and uncle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, she did not. Far from it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 She did all the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 All the washing, all the baking, all everything. Everybody else's - looked after everybody. That had babies and all that sort of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh she used to mend did mother. Oh she did that, used to have to mend - was all patched up you see, everything were patched. She was always careful, everything was patched. Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she actually make the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. She were no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207  sewer,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  no, only mending. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were the clothes you got new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. We used to get them from other people. Anybody that she could get them from. 'Cos these people that washed would happen give her something you see. Yes. Too true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How would you go on for shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Ah now, just thinking about shoes. I - I remember we lived in one house and the lady give us some shoes and I was - and my }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 feet's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  been bad because of them 'cos they were nice shoes and I - I wore them and I shouldn't have done you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They were ill fitting were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they didn't fit me but they were nice ones you see. Yes. But I can remember just - just them bits of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So most of your shoes were given to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - the most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You can't remember buying any shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, I can remember buying - I can remember - I were going to act in a concert and I can remember going to one place and buying shoes and - me mother had to pay for them so much a week, she couldn't affor
d to pay for them but she would get me them, for this one thing. I can't remember - I know the shop where she went. We called it Birkwell's in - in - Bradford Street. But it isn't there now, the house is pulled down but it was Birkwell's in Bradford Stree
t. And I can remember that one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 incident}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  you see, she had to pay for them every week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So that was a sort of special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it was a special one, very special one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your father used to repair the shoes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can neve
r remember him - that - but - I can't - you see we used to wear clogs for work at Oakworth, and we used to call at the cloggers when we came home and we used to call there and get these irons put on. And we used to call 'em - we'd only have one pair of sh
oes for Sunday pair. Used to have Sunday clogs in them days. Don't have Sunday clothes now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your father helping your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, he did, he used to be - he was a right good sort of a man. Used
 to do lots of jobs but they did - they seemed - men in them days they just seemed to go to work and come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The hours were so long weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, they seemed to work a long while, because they used to start at six, work 'til half past fi
ve, well they was tired you see. I don't remember - he might - he would do because he never went anywhere, never went to pubs or anything of that my a father, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were at home before you left school did you have any tasks you had to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember what your jobs were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Scrub that floor in that house. In the one we lived in Mill Lane, where there were a great big kitchen it was a flagged floor and we used to have to scrub it in our turns. And th
ere were great big stone sink, and we had to wash up in there and then scrub the sink all down. You know, all them sort of things we used to have before that - before ever I went to work we used to wash up in our turns. And scrub this floor. Stone floor o
nce a week. And, you know, we used to wash our hair and get bathed in a dolly tub and thing in front of - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember the older children helping the little ones with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I mean to say we all used to help one another because
 - well we would do wouldn't we because there weren't the money to go and get things done them days. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And did the little ones help the older ones with jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I expect - I expect we all used to help. I can't remember anything much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember being expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, we did. We had - had to go to bed by half - by eight o'clock when we were thought we'd grown up a little bit. To go to bed by eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember who put you to bed, was it your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, mother always put us to bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I can't remember that. As soon as we could, as soon as we could yes, we had to get upstairs your
self you know. As soon as you could. Because there's too many children you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You must have shared the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we did, yes, brothers and sisters. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you manage the sleeping arrangements of the whole family, where did you all sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - I can remember sleeping with my sister Lily and our George. That was her that came down on Saturday, old - the next one to me lower down. I can remember three of us being in bed and happen four of us, I know we were in this bed, n
ot sleeping that way, you know, that way. There's more room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Across the width of the bed sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Yes, we did, we slept across the width - yes. Three of us and many a time four, yes, I can - I can't remember about - I know we used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So all the children would sleep in two double beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, there - there was two double bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  in that room. And we used to have to sleep in there. No bathroom or anything you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember where your grandma and uncle would sleep at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Where mother and father slept.? Yes, yes. Oh they'd have a room on their own I should say, I can't remember. I expect some of them slept in there I don't know, can't remember that. No, I can't remember mother and father, where 
- you see father died when we were so little, well - I was only - I was - well I was eleven you see, twelve nearly. No, I wasn't - I were thirteen when father died. And - but I can't remember a lot about that. It's only little pieces I can remember.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you used to bath in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have a zinc bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, a dolly tub. I can remember getting bathed in dolly tub when I'm going to bet married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you couldn't sit down in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, had to stand up but - I can remember that as clear as anything. Getting bathed in the dolly tub when I were going to get married.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A dolly tub was sort of barrel shaped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I have one in the cellar now. Yes. And rings - iron rings round it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were small where did you used to have your meals, did you have them in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. In the kitchen, oh at Sunday afternoon we had 'em in the parlour. We called it the parlour, yes. Yes, we used to have 'em in there, just at Sunday afternoon
. There - these 'ere places they was kept as parlours in them days, they called them the parlour. Used to have a certain table cover to put on, it always had to be put on at Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did your mother cook, in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I expect so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember what her cooking equipment was, did she have a gas stove or was it a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh she wouldn't have a gas oven, on the fire. On the fire. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember what time of the day you'd have your breakfast and would you all be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well we have to go - be to school for half past eight you see. I don't know. Oh we'd have some bread and dripping or something - we used to have bread and dripping because salt put on it. Many and many a time, and a bit of bread and sugar a 
bit of sugar put on. Oh we did that. Yes. Sugar put on it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would that be about eight o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I daresay it would be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would your father be there his breakfast or would he be at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - he were up to he died I should think. But I can't remember. I remember having this bread and dripping and - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have anything different on certain days such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh my mother used to make lots of dumplings. And - and a boiled pudding in a cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That would be for your dinner would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Dumplings. Broth - sheep head broth we used to have. Sheep head broth. Yes. Then me father used to - me mother - me mother used to wrap the brains up in a cloth and they were separate and daddy had to have them you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 see}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  with
 his - salt and pepper on, they were his luxury. And we used to have dumplings, you see, dumplings and put in this broth. All vegetables in you see. Still it did you good didn't it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember having anything special for breakfast on Saturday or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, never - I never remember having anything special, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did you have your dinner, what time of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh, when we came home from the mill you see at half past twelve. And I - be back at school for one o'clock
 - for half past one. And them that were going for half time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your father come home for his dinner as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I daresay he did, I don't know. I don't think ever he worked anywhere where he had to be away a lot. Don't remember a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You told me about having }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 sheep\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  head broth for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember having anything else for dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I can't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At the weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We - we should have, we should have but I can't remember. This thin
g just - stick in me mind. We had a pan on the stove - on the fireplace that they boil in you see and that thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about teas, what would you have at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh a bit of jam I expect. Can't remember, we had - never had luxuries - never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Not even on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Well, yes, as Sunday we used to have something a little bit different. When - I can't - think we had when we were wed - when I was married and that were a tin of salmon and we thought that was a luxury. But I don't remembe
r what we used to have, no. No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she did, all her own. Everything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she ever make any jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't remember her making jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she ever make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh used to have treacle and sulphur. We used to have to line up for it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What was it supposed to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well it just made you go to the toilet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Kept regular?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, it did, yes, sulphur and - brimstone and treacle that's what they called it. All mixed up together in a pint pot, used to have to line up and all grab this 'ere spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember her brewing any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. She wouldn't have a beer people, no, we never had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have a garden or an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we had no garden, no, no garden. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never grew your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I never remember anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would they buy fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh she'd have to buy - she used to buy jam pots - you know, call him - man that was in Keighley, call him Johnny Pot or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That was a nickname was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. He was a right little man ever such a little man. He lived at the bottom of Nares Street and we used to buy from Johnny Pot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Why was he called Johnny Pot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know - 'cos he was a little one, that were all. He was a little old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 wizened}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  old man. That's all I can remember about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So they didn't have an allotment or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So they didn't keep any hens or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. We didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember how many times a week you'd have meat, would it be every day or just once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh if we got it once it'd be about all - 
happen a Sunday we had some meat. I should I should say so, I can't remember, I know me mother used to make Yorkshire puddings but beyond that I can't remember anything else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember getting any extra meat from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. No. No. Never did anything we didn't ought to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember a friend who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, well they do, you know, but we didn't. I never remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember ever seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Ah yes, many a time, yes, many time. Do without that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You said when you had the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 sheep\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  head boiled the brains were always kept for your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Oh it's true is that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that your father usually had more than the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well, they used to do it in them days didn't they, the men had to have a bigger - a bigger portion than you. Well I - perhaps he - he would do you know, I know men was men in them days. They was there just to - oh I c
ouldn't - I don't know - can't think. They were there just to get the children the - in them days, men were for that purpose, to go to work, keep the family and get the family and that was in them days in my idea. And didn't do a lot of - didn't do things
 like they do today. That's my idea of men in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were all sat at the table having a meal, did you all used to sit round the table in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we had a big square table, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You had another table in the parlour for weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, another square table, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you allowed to talk during the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. We hadn't. We hadn't to read or anything either, Sunday we hadn't read I - get no books or papers out. Oh no. Oh we weren't - no, father's word was law you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Throughout a meal at any time had you to sit quietly?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we did used to have to sit quietly at the meal, yes, we did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh eat everything. If you don't eat it get away from the table you have to. Yes. Well they hadn't nothing else to give you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would your parents attitude be if you did leave anything uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - I don't know, I can't - I can't just remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You probably wouldn't leave very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we didn't - get what you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If there was something on the table you wanted such as the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you hav
e to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, you could ask, yes, you could say, will you pass that or that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you ever able to have a second helping of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, you had it there on your plate and that was - yes. That was your lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents expect you to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. No they never were like that, my parents, no. No we weren't brought up like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you ever allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, you hadn't to bring anything to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well all left it together you see when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You waited until everyone had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, yes, we had to wait, yes. And then that were finished then mother used to move the things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And all he family sat at the table for the meals?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We all sat together, yes. Had to wait 'til they - 'til they're all there and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you always have the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we did, yes, it was - oh that's my place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you all have a chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or did some of you have to stand at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Some of us - yes, the younger ones. Oh used to have to wait sometimes 'til the other's had done if - if there were anybod
y else coming at all, you see, they'd have to wait 'til - well it depends on who was here like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 There'd be eleven of you all told wouldn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you sometimes had to wait for your turn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, had to wait for yo
ur turns at the table 'cos the - the table there - they couldn't put no extension on it you know them days. There were the table and it were there - you know scrubbing there - white top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How was the meal served, did your mother put all the food out on the plates and then give you the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that's right, yes. It wasn't - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 , it wasn't in tureens, no. It was put on the - on the - on the plates. She used to get the plates there and do it that way and this is yours and get on with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What order would she serve you in, would she serve the little ones first or the big ones or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, the little ones always had to wait. Oh father and the older ones had to be served.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember your younger brothers and sisters being quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you know where they used to sit before they could feed themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well we had a high chair, I can remember that. Remember we had a high chair, a fixture you know and they - the younger ones used to sit in that, and a tray in front of it. That's all I can remember of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would feed them, would it be your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Always mother, it's always me mother that fed them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she was, yes, she was quite easy to get on with you know and all that kind of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was she an affectionate sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she was, very nice, yes, she was a nice person my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she show affection to you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes she did, she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 showed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 you affection. - And that's - I think that's where I get it from you see. I feel as though I could - I can - oh I can hold anybody, I can touch anybody, you know what I mean? Lots of people can't touch anybody and they won't be touche
d you see, but I could - touch anybody, in a right sort of a way you see and - and - yes, I think it helps you in life. I think - it helps you in life. No, but I do - I do think it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you had any worries before you left school could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - I don't think so, I don't think that mother - I think she had a lot to do with first one and another and me father dying and I don't think she did a right lot of sharing of these 'ere - I don't - I never remember having m
any worries, I know one girl that went to school when I did and - she were kind of a bully, you know, there generally is isn't there, I can just remember this one. She was kind of a bully and she - I know mother used to say, if I could get hold her what I
'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 with her you know. And I can remember this girl, remember her name and I can remember seeing her. It's funny that isn't it in your life. And - but beyond that I can't remember a lot about it. I don't think we would go to mother with a lot of troubles,
 she's say I've plenty of me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 own}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh father were nice, he was a nice man. I can't remember a right lot but what I can remember about him I liked him. I liked him myself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that he showed affection, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I should say he would do, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you ever remember telling him any of your worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't - no, I don't think - I think - never remember that we had a lot to - we didn't
 worry about things like they do today, no, I don't think that we did have a - no, I don't think we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know - well - we just used to live a normal life you know, I can't remember 
that - you was expected to do - I know - you know, they soon give you a smack at side - you know, clip at side of face we used to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was that if you said anything you shouldn't have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh we hadn't to say anything we shouldn't do to your mother. Treat your mother as she ought to be treat you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This was with respect was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you like them to respect them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, your parents you had to do. Your parents was parents weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 How would you say that your parents brought you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh very good. Yes, very good, you never had to be bullied then you see. Was always happy at home, very poor but very happy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Very, very poor. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would your parents say if you went home and told them another child had hit you or hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh well, they would soon be saying, coming on, we'll go and see them, and they used to go to school and see these other children them days. Yes, they used to see
m to do that I think in them days. Your mother'd go to school and - I know I did with our girls, I can remember - had me photo in paper once. Can't remember that properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would they ever say that you should hit back yourself if somebody had hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, they used to tell you, you know, that - I don't think that's right but they did used to say - well they'd say, you - you hit 'em back. And they used to say this, you must have done something wrong for them to hit you, you see. Now what - what's 
the bottom of it, you see, there was something that you'd done wrong for them to hit you. But - I - I don't remember a lot - Oh don't think were - it were very hard put to hit at school. No.
\par 
