\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh I don't think that - I think if they were to come back now and see - see what you are and you've - your daughters are and your sons or whatever you have, I think they would be agreeable surprised. I do really. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Yes, I think - they never think - they could alter like you have done because we're - as I tell you, we were very, very poor and therefore if you are poor well - you know, you lived a poor life didn't you.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You think they expected you to remain poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 I think that t
hey did do in that - they never expected you to get - get up - no, I wouldn't like to say that word - anything different but to get up to be just that little bit different, some people, I've met some of them, they're very, very rough you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well they wou
ldn't expect you to be like that you see, to be a rough - rough was kind. Was always poor but good you know. Good - no, not good, I don't mean that, but good in a certain way. Brought up to respect people. We was brought up to respect other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, yes, religion were very important in our life. And that's all - I can't remember - but it was important in our life. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh -
 terrible. Oh I never heard - I never heard my husband swear the whole time I had him, now that's funny. You can say that about a man. I don't say he didn't, I'm not saying he didn't - 'cos you don't know what they do when they're alone, and I never heard
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 swear, I never heard me father swear, no. Nor me brothers. Me brother comes here now and I never - he might do, I'm not saying they don't but not in front of me. I think they respect me. I do really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - no. No. You sit there. Children should be seen and not heard. That was our attitude there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you did something your parents disapproved of and they were cross about what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well you'd go to bed. Yes, you'd go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you said sometimes they would give you a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh you'd get a - a sidewinder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would it be on the face?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, sidewinder we used to call 'em. Give you a sidewinder and - and then go to bed and stop there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would do this, would it be your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, me father. Me father would - not often - didn't - you know, we weren't bad. But if you were bad that'd be what you'd get. Not like they do today say - promising 'em. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 
Get in and give 'em a sidewinder, do 'em good.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So it would be quite occasional that this happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, very occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother ever do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't remember ever me mother hitting us, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished in this way and what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I can't remember. I - no, I can't remember ever being punished, I can't really. No I don't think ever I - was,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it mainly the boys who were punished in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it was, yes, they were - yo
u know, they had all lad in them you know like they have today but - remember once me brother - I was going out one night, this is after I were married, I were going that one night and went upstairs to get changed and he came out of another room as I were
 going in with a sheet over him and saving it like this and - and he had to go to bed for that, I can remember little bits like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And he frightened you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - I never went out that night after. I was going with a boy, young fellow, and they ha
d to go and tell him that I - I - I couldn't go out. Nearly fainted you see. Them things upset me you see. But that - that'd be what they'd be punished for you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that the ideas that you received about to have, would you get them from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd get them from both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you had a birthday would it be any different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No birthday parties. No, just at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Nothing special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never remember having anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't have any guests at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, I can remember always having a Christmas tree and the house trimmed up you know and we used to have spiced pigs and - on the three - spice - sugary pig and a sugary watch and it had little t
hings on - on a stalk - on a band, like that, and a watch at the end, that were on the end of that, and we use to hang our stockings up and we used to have an orange and an apple and a few nuts put in our stocking, we thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 There wouldn't be any toys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. Toys were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you would be given these things off the Christmas tree?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh they were - oh they were on the bed. On the bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would they take the sugar things off the tree and give them to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Ye
s. Yes. They - yes, we used to trim the tree up with - no, nothing expensive you know, just the sugar pigs and a watch you know and a little bit of tinsel around that was all there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any musical instruments at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We had an harmonium. Harmonium. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who played it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
My - I did. I had fourteen lessons, that was all, and it was a shilling a lesson. I can remember this. And - my uncle who lived with us and he bought this harmonium and - he paid - he said, I'll pay fo
r your lessons, you see. Well it - it was - and - he'd stand by you the whole time and I know the lady that used to - give me, the lessons and all and he'd stand by you the whole time beating time and I just got fed up with it and I finished with it, you 
see. And I just had fourteen lessons. I can remember that. That was all. We had nothing else, only that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And no one else you could play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your fourteen lessons enable you to play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I - I never took it up, never carried on with it you see. No, I never carried on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So it was never used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well then I expect he'd sell it, I've forgot now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, nobody. My sister - me eldest sister, she was in - what they call
 it - Sunday afternoon - a lot of men and women used to - Sunday - Sunday Circle, and she was in the choir at the Sunday}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207  Circle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 was me sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would she ever sing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she used to sing many a time at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever all sing together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh yes, we used to always have get - you know, have little does of a - you know, they used to bring their friends and - we had to make our own amusement you see. Yes, we would have little sing-songs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your parents playing any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I dare - yes, I think they did, yes. And me uncle - Uncle Ben used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would they play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - oh, I'll tell you what we used to - used to - I can remember one game we used to have. We'd put a chair 
there and a chair here and put a - a brush - oh brushtail you see I'm talking Yorkshire - a brushtail through a clothes basket. And we used to sit in it like this you see with this brushtail across here like and there were pennies put on each corner of th
e chair like that. And we used to have to try and knock a penny off with a paper there and that - and if you - of course if you turned turned round to knock these other pennies off you tipped over you see, they all used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 burst}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  of laughing. Remember that -
 doing that a lot, always had this - this game you see and - and what sit we used to play, another game a lot - oh what the world was it, I've forgot now - oh I can't think, we used to play a lot of games, oh well going outside and playing }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 postman\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  knock and going in the kitchen and - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember there being any books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we didn't have a lot of books, no we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would there be some?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, there'd be - well there'd be the Bible in amon
gst all the others you know. That was what we used to have to read. We used to get books sometimes but we had to - only read 'em at certain times you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I - I don't know - I just - can't remember that. Can't remember wh
ether we used to get newspapers or not, I expect we did - would do, but not - we didn't have to waste no money you see, it was always - always thinking about money you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember them getting any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. We never got any magazines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your mother or father reading, sitting reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well my mother couldn't read, do you know, she couldn't write. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, but mother couldn't. She c
ould neither read nor write could me mother. We used to read to her. Yes. We used to read to her and she loved it. She loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 She never learnt to read until she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. She never - right - right to her dying, she used to put her cross for h
er - at the side of her name. No, she couldn't read couldn't my mother. You see, when she was young, our age, she used to have to follow the - not the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 plough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - in a - gleaning she used to call it. She used to go gleaning and she'd get threepence a week for it. Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 she\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 have to do - used - they used to have to pay threepence a week to go to school. Well her mother couldn't afford to pay this threepence a week, and she used to - she were glad of her bringing this threepence a week home. Money was tight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 She must have lived in an agricultural area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 She must have done, yes, I think - yes, she must - I remember her telling about this gleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You said your mother couldn't read at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your father reading aloud to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I never remember me father reading, I don't think he did do but we used to read to her. We used to read to her and she used to - we used to carry on with a serial you know and read a serial, me and my sister, we used to read to her a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This was later after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that's it, yes, after we've been to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family, you'd remember your father's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I remember me father's funeral. Yes, I remember me father's funeral. D
o you mind, I were only thirteen and I had a long frock on with brushed braid on the bottom and a hook, not a hook, clip - clip on there and then it used - we used to put it in a belt here. Oh - silly at that age. And I can remember this 'ere - this 'ere 
d
ress sweeping on the floor - when - oh me father died - can't remember a lot about - about the funeral beyond that. I can remember me mother was very distressed about it 'cos it left us all very little. But I can't remember a lot - lot about - can't remem
b
er where we went. And we would go somewhere because we - we always chapel and - we went to Albert Street Baptist Chapel you know. You know where that is don't you, bottom of - of Highfield Lane, but I never remember anything much about his funeral. We sho
uld have it as cheap as ever we could because we couldn't afford to pay you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember if there would be horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, would be horses, yes. Horse drawn coach you know. I can remember my husbands so it's only about seven years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did all the children attend that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we all went, yes, we all had - and we wore deep black you know in them days. Crepe round your hat and - we all wore deep black.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember who attended, was it just your mother and you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 All his family yes, all his family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You can't remember aunts and uncles or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I can't remember, I expect there would but I can't remember. Remember me father dying, died in Bradford infirmary. He had a - something wrong with his s
tomach. And it burst you see, it'd be an ulcer I should say, and it burst and he died, they took him there, he wasn't - they didn't used to bother taking him to hospital like they do now you know, I'm talking about it - about sixty years ago you know. Oh 
yes, going for seventy years ago. Well it's a long time isn't it you know. You can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were small do you remember ever being taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't remember, no, I think we had enough home wi
th us - own family without - I - I remember - one lady that I used to go with her daughter and her mother must have gone out. This one night, Saturday night, they called her Annie Briggs. It's funny this all happened in Mill Lane. And I can remember going
 in staying in her house one night and that's all I can remember about it. Funny is that. Always remember that one thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember going out with your parents to visit anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No I don't, no. I don't think ever they went out much. 
No. After they got married in them days they stopped at home and that were that. Have the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you ever taken shopping with either of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't - I can't remember. No. No. We did go shopping when I - on - on Bockthorn to a ladie
s on there we used to go and get the shopping on there. But I've forgotten what they called her. In a - a shop on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would that be with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, me brother. Me - me brother used to go, when we've been took the washing back to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Burwin's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  'cos it was on that way you see. I fancy that it's in the rain - can't remember a lot about the shopping. No, I can't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes I did, used to go a lot with just me father. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would you do when you went out with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Just go out for a walk, we used to go Lower Bank and see some gardens up there, I can remember, I know just where they were now. We used to go there - I was me father's pet, they all used to tell me that. Th
at I was - and he always went and he always - he'd call me Esther, he used to call me Essie, you know what it - what it is, they generally do look after one don't they, bother with one more than the other. They always used to say I was father's pet, which
 I was I think if I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember and other outings with hour parents, did you ever go answer on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - no, we used to go walking sometimes, happen go a walk you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you take a picnic with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to take a picnic, yes, we had to take with us what - we weren't going in anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would all the family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well yes, I daresay they would - all - happen - happen those that were younger than me you see would.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - we used to go to - up Slippery Ford and all round - round the top up there you see. I can remember that like but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd walk a mile or two wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - used to walk a lot of miles. We didn't - yes, used to walk you see, always walked, there were no buses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And that was your Bank Holiday treat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that was it, yes, you had day out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd never go to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never. Never. Not 'til after I were married a long - lot of years after I were married. Never went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never actually went to the seaside until after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Never saw it. No. No, 'til after - years after I were married. I remember once I was going to g
o with daddy, when we were courting this was, we were going to go Skegness and he slept along and - and I was there at the station but he never come, so I went home and I must nicely got back when he came. So we never went any where, we was think Skegness
 that day, and I never - never been. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you never actually went away to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Never. No. Never did. Not when I had me honeymoon I - my honeymoon, I got married on to Saturday, I went to work at Monday morning. I did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you tell me how you used to spend your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well we always went to Sunday school, that were our Sunday. Get up and have your breakfast and went to Sunday school in the morning, Sunday 
school in the afternoon you see, we stayed for our dinners, Sunday school in the afternoon and - beyond that - this is when I was at home I mean. Yes. I can't remember - Sunday night I expect we had a - you know - a - we'd sit round and tell the tale I ex
pect, I can't think. No, I always used to go to Sunday school with me dad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we had some clothes. I can remember we had a - a - we used to have the anniversary at Sundays, Slack Lane this is, anni
versary, and go in the morning in our old clothes to practice. Then go in the afternoon with - all dressed up and - we used to put cold tea on our hair and curled it. Cold tea - oh sweetened cold tea made it frizzy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You sort of set it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Make
 it frizzy with the sweetened cold tea. Used to put that on our hair and - and go with all pins up and all that sort of thing and the old clothes in the morning have a practice and then go and have the anniversary in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd have to walk all the way home and get changed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. To walk home yes. Oh - always had to walk. I mean - well there weren't no buses or anything then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents think it wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh yes. Sunday had to be Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you not be allowed to play any sort of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, we didn't have to play and we didn't have to read anything. Sunday had to be Sunday in them days. It was just Sunday. Didn't pick a newspaper up you know, if - I - I don't know wheth
er there was any or not but - you wouldn't - read the Bible you know of a Sunday. Had to do. Hadn't a lot of books about you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You attended Slack Lane Baptist church didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Chapel, yes. Yes, it was a chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, they did, yes, they were married there, yes, oh yes, and - mother didn't go a lot because of course he had all these children to look after. She'd cook and rest a little while but I used to go with me father.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents attend fairly regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Father did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just your father did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he go as often as you did to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He used to go with me, yes, he always - he was the chairman, they called it being chairman - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . He was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So he'd be there as often as you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. And I know he used to - he used to have concerts you know and I can remember one little thing that I used to stand up and say. Ladies and gentlemen, chairman and all, if you stand on your feet you'll never }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
all. I thought it were wonderful 'cos I used to say that. Used to go - standing there - up - you know, on the top and say this. I thought it were wonderful 'cos we could just say this 'ere you know. Eeh it's funny. Brings back a lot of memories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 say}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 you went to church as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well only since I - probably since I knew daddy. My husband changed me to - to the - Church of England, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you went to Slack lane you'd go to Sunday school morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would there be a proper chapel service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At night. In the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, we used to come home then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would your father go to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, he didn't go at night, no, he used to go in the morning. Well, he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 
superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember there ever being any Sunday school outings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I don't think they had it - never remember going out - out anywhere, no, I don't. They used to go to the - a minister's to tea occasion
ally, they called him Mr Evans, and we used to go to - he had a daughter called Mary, daughter called Mary and we - I used to go with her sometimes and - great favour they'd ask us to tea you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he invite the whole Sunday school to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, only just one or two of us, yes, and - remember I used to go, I don't know about anybody else but I used to go. She always lived near - nearby Slack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it because of your father being }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, yes. There's three houses nearl
y by Slack, do you know Slack, well there's three - well we lived in that middle one there. We used to have - remember cutting bread up for communion. Isn't funny little things that comes in your mind. Can remember - me mother used to bake her own bread a
nd cut a thick slice off and put it all in squares like that. Don't have that now but we used to have that for communion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you lived in Slack Lane at one time did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we lived up there, yes, we lived in that little house up there, I can r
emember that. See, I can - thought - thoughts come in your mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the Sunday school organise any picnics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. Never went anywhere. No, you didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Didn't they have any processions at Whitsuntide?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Yes, we did used to wal
k in procession. I don't know what - what holiday it was - well it was on holiday and we used to walk in procession. We did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the procession go somewhere or did it do a circular to up and back to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I - do you know Isaac Holdings Hal
l, well we used to go - oh we had to take our shoes off - take our shoes or clogs off whatever they were, we didn't walk around in clogs but - we - when Isaac Holding were dead this is what I mean we were called from school and we had to take our clogs of
f at the entrance hall and walk and see him laid - laid -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it in the big house or in the hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
In the - he were in the - I don't know, he were in a big place that were only thing I could say but this - the holidays we used to walk round his gr
ounds. He used to open his grounds for us at a certain holiday, we used to walk in procession all round his - and I can remember going through the hot houses you know and he had all these lovely flowers and grapes and - and we'd go through all that you se
e walk all round to go in on Slaymaker Lane and come out near Marlborough Park or anything. That's all we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never went to a field anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Not - I did when I went to a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Baptist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - Albert Street but not Slack, no. No, no. Slack was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Baptist}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you when you went to Albert Street, was that later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Eeh I don't know, I were courting a long time when I went to Albert Street. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Oh I went to Albert Street a long, long time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, used to have - used to go - go on platfor
m and have little does at Pancake Tuesdays. I can remember what we used to sing. Was - you know, making the pan cakes. Mixing flour and slat and eggs and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At the actual chapel hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, at - in Albert Street, had a school down in the cellar. We used to go to that. This is when I was a bit bigger you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember any other social activities being organised by the chapel, either at Slack Lane or at Albert Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well at Albert Street we used to have a field day and we used to 
go up Spring Gardens Lane, ever so far up Spring Gardens Lane and have a field day and we used to get a bun and a cup of tea. We had to take us own mug. And they used to give us a currant bun and then we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You had a procession to it did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, and we used to have races. That was how they used to enjoy their selves you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would this be about the time you started work when you were about twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I daresay that I happen be seventeen - sixteen or seventeen then I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At Slack Lane do you remember any social occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they ever give any concerts or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - no, only this - we used to just go - used to - we used to have little does among ourselves, I can't remember anythin
g like particular, I - I know I can remember that little thing that I used to say, but - no, not a lot of things I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the chapel have any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I - oh yes, well white - white ribbon as joined, hear them talk now - the
y drink wines and all that sort of things, and say, oh you won't want any, your little white ribbon in you know. Still cal it - Bank of Hope we used to have, yes. I was a member of the Band of Hope. Member of the Band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What were the activities of the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh we used to have little does, I've forgotten now what we did, we used to have little parties you know at the Band of Hope. A lot of us going together and then having games and that at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
The Christian Endeavour. Christian Endeavour, that was - it was a - a club - not a youth club, no, didn't have youth clubs, it was a little meeting you know, but they were all - I tell you, we had nothing a only all t
hese religious things you see and I had a - a little brooch - there were - I can remember it - and it was a little thing like that and it had two chains and C - C.E. - Christian Endeavour down here. I have it - I haven't that but I've another tiepin that 
daddy had with C.E1 on. He was in the Christian Endeavour too. That's all as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 There wasn't any other club at all organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't remember - only Band of Hope and Christian Endeavour, that's all there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At home did your father say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He didn't, no, he didn't, no, no. No what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you say prayers before going to bed at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we all had to say prayers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you say them individually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, all together, yes. Father used to say them. It was father's job to say - say the prayers before you went to bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your father take an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes he did, he was a great Liberal. Yes. Polling day he used to have a - he used to go abou
t in a trap. Who was it that went with him, I've }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 forgotten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 now, and he used to be the man that went round fetching them all in you know, and they used to have a trap and he had a great long whip and a yellow bow on it, I can remember these little bits you see. He were always a great }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 Liberal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 , always was a Liberal were me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know why he was a Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, the only - well he wouldn't be a Conservative and there were only Liberals and Conservatives then, and he wouldn't be a Conservati
ve 'cos we were very poor and there was only two classes then, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You think it was because he was working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he was a working class man, yes, and that's why they were - why they were Liberals you see. Oh yes, he would great Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your father voting at a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he used to vote yes. Always vote Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently form their employers, do you 
know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't - no, I don't - only I know that he was really - I used to call him a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 bigoted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  Liberal. Yes. He thought nobody else had a right to have their opinion, he were rather strong, th
ought nobody else had a right to have their opinion, they all - everybody had to be Liberals that come anywhere near your house because - there were one or two classes and we didn't bother with the top - the better class, you see, we didn't bother with th
at class of people and everybody had to - oh Liberals and - Conservatives then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think your father was a member of the Liberal party at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I expect he was - would be wouldn't he, I don't know, just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you remember him working for the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. He did. He used to go out in this trap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember him being politically active at other times other than elections?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think he would, no. No. No. Used to have these meetings round about election time you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He would go to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I would go with him - everywhere with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't know, couldn't tell you. Couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother have any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 interest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  at all outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, only washing and baking and looking after the children, having another child or having another child, that's all the mothers did in them days. It was what a woman was for in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So she never went out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12735578\charrsid4211207 
No, I don't think ever my mother - I never remember my mother going - oh no, I think many a time, t'would be lovely if she could come back and see all these little things that we have, vacuums and all these things that we hav
e now, it'd be lovely for her to come back and see them.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh it'd be six o'clock. They wouldn't finish 'til half past five. And they always had to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would he do most evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - don't know, never remember going out - very little. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He never went to any clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, he didn't, no. No. Never went to pubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never remember him being a sportsman, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He never attended the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or had a bet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your father or mother belong to a savings club such as a boot club or a sick club or a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. They hadn't, no - no - well - I think that 
- now did me mother once - I think she happen did once - have some money some - you know - about sixpence a week or something of that in for when me father died, I think she did have - I don't know whether it were insurance or what you know, I've forgot n
o
w, but I think she did have just about sixpence a week. You see, all this money was tied up, we used to have doctor's bills you see and - a doctor would come, you could send for a doctor in them days and they'd come and you had a doctor bill but it - it -
 a doctor might come and you'd pay sixpence week - for ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Forever - no, forever, the doctor might pay - chancing he had to come again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you paid into a sort of club and the club would pay out the doctor's bill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Y
es. Yes. Well this man, a man, a - we used to call him a doctor man, he used to come and pick the - yes - well a man came to collect it he used to give it to the doctor, so much collected you see. Doctors weren't well off then like they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you say when your father died your mother got a bit of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she did, just a - a pound or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think that was a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I daresay it was, I remember her - me mother never had anything much to do with any insurance
. Because her couldn't - they couldn't do it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh ever so well. Ever so well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I did, me brother that comes and I always felt close to him, I always have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was the next youngest to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was next to me, yes, he's eighty, well he'll be eighty-one 20th of this month.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Two years younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well they're all two years. And I 
had a brother killed in the war, he was two years younger than him. It'd be the 19-14 wouldn't it. The first war. I can remember that. I can remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 As a child who did you play with, your brothers and sisters or neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Well we had - yes, we had a few neighbours you know, we had a few neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You would play out with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to play out. Play at skipping and hopscotch and checks, all them sort of things we used to play, I can remember quite 
well playing at skipping and pies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  ball.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you play these games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the street. In the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't have a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, no, hadn't got a garden, no playing fields, we used to play in the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you played piesball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember anything else you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh at skipping, checks, and - we used to throw a ball and there'd be a can and we had to knock the can over or throw it in the can, all that sort of thing you know, we used to make our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you allowed to get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we used to get ever so dirty and we used to wear pinnies, white pinnies you know. A white }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 pinny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  and they were washed every - clean pinny on every morning over top of your dress 'cos there was 
no fancy dresses on you know. Only white pinny, I can remember having embroidery all on it, it were all ironed you know, nicely. Yes, I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, yes, we could play with anybody, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your parents didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, they didn't, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You belonged to the Band of Hope and the Christian Endeavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there any other youth organisation you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't remember anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The Girl Guides weren't going then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, well the - no, they weren't no. There - just this Sunday Circle that me father used to go to and my oldest sister about I wasn't old enough to go there and they used to open Sunday every month and we used to go to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any hobbies while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you do any knitting, sewing, crocheting, embroidery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I - I expect we did do but I can't remember what we used to do in our spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Cigarette cards or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't have a garden so you wouldn't do any gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go fishing or for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Oh for walks, always we had to go to walks, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we never had bicycles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you just went for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would you go with mainly, you occasionally went with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 With father, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it nearly always with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Or - me older sisters you know. My sister called Sarah, a sister called Mary Ann, I mean I used to think it was a great day if I could go with them, walks you know. Oh yes. Two bigger ones, used to think it was a great day if they said, come on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever take part in any sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never, no. No never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never theatres.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No fear, we used to go temperance hall sometimes, see magic lanterns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That was connected with the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 With the Band of Hope, yes. The Sunday night after chapel we used to go to the temperance hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you wouldn't be going to any cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. They had - well there wasn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . No. Weren't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents give you any pocket money while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to get about tuppence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You got it every week did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I got sixpence when I were married so - sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you spend the tuppence a week on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh used to be two - we used to get tiger nuts up - up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 Lidgett's}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . Ha'porth of tiger nuts up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 Lidgett\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
. Used to make it last out you see because if we had any lef
t me mother used to borrow it off us again. Then when we get it a back and we used to spend it. And - wild honey I think we - wild honey, it was like in a piece of brown piece and we used to break it up. I think they called it wild honey, it was sweet.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it a sort of toffee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it was a kind of a toffee. Then we used to get everlasting sweets, see, all what we used to buy, everlasting sticks and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 Spanish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  ribbons and I used to love Spanish ribbons they used to pull 'em down like that and they'd
 roll up. Make 'em last a long while. Oh dear, isn't it awful. When you think - you know really when you think about all this it's - how you used to enjoy yourself with a little bit of - aye, that's the truth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember anyone outside the home helping }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 your mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  to look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, she never - they didn't. She used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No relations or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. Never used anybody - aunts - aunts and that used to come to have a little holiday, a day or so holi
day and then go back ago. Aunt Nancy and - they'd happen -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Aunt Nancy - Bu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 nley, Aunt Nancy and Uncle Dick. That were me mother's brother were Dick and this were his wife, Aunt Nancy, they used to come sometimes. Just o
n a little day or so holiday. Aye, he used to walk over many times - you know Furness, Furness, well he used to walk up at Furness to Burnley - Oakworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He used to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Many and may - I've walked there myself many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It must be about eighteen or nineteen miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I've walked there myself many a time with me Uncle Ben. Yes I have.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Stayed there overnight and come back the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Stayed at me aunt Nancy's. They had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 shop and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  we thought they were right well off with having a shop. Yes. But we could only stay one night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It must have been at least sixteen miles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
It was a long way over Furness but it were quite interesting 'cos it was all moors and reservoirs and all that. I go over there sometime when my daughter comes from Birmingham, go round that way, you know. Yes, it's funny is all these things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It's very high up isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it is, very high and we go down a road like that to Wyeco}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 
llar Dene. Been to Wyecollar De}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 ne many a time. Many and ma
y a time I've been to Wyecollar Dene, we used to go to a place called the Big Dam. That's up round Slippery Ford. There's a big dam. I went round there not long since with a relation, well she's a distant relation mind, she had a car. She said, where you 
l
ike to go? I said, round Slippery Ford and Big Dam. Yes, well we didn't go right to Big Dam, she says you can't get the car there, you've got to walk. Yes, she said - she said, well I'll take as far as I can. Coming near pinnacle, walked all over them pla
ces. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
I don't know. Can't remember ever me mother being poorly, she were only about poorly a fortnight before she died and all. She were eighty-four when she died and I never remember me mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1906073\charrsid4211207 
being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 poorly much. She'd have children but some - the neighbours would come in and do for her you know. The time that she - they had to stop in bed in them days you know, about a week didn't they, they used to do, oh yes, when they had a baby
. I mean, it'd do them good now to lie in bed but they don't you see, they get up. But they used to stay in bed for about a week, and neighbours used to come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember this, can you remember your younger brothers and sisters being born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I can remember one - I can remember me mother had one and it was stillborn, I can remember that baby being born, yes, I can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know, I must have only been a child, I can - I think about it many a time, I know me f
ather bundled us all off to bed. And I know mother's water must have broke and I remember this piece, her water must have broke and - oh I forgot that things on - well, I mean them sort of things you see - yes, and - and he bundled us all to be}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  and the ne
xt morning this baby was laid out on the couch, you see, I can - and it must have been - it were born dead. And that was our seventh baby. I can remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So she had another one after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, all the little bit piecings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207  (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  up and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They actually laid the baby out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, it was laid out on the couch, I remember it quite plainly. And I don't know how - how they buried it or anything but it were laid out on the couch. No, they - the next morning when we got up t
here were this baby there and me mother were quite her normal size but that's how - how they used to be in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - me mother had - one or two brothers and sisters, not father. And I ca
n remember - never remember anybody belonging to me father. He came up from Ely and I never - I don't know what he did or anything. I never remember anybody belonging to me father. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So your mother had one or two relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh every - oh used to wee - well Uncle Ben lived with us, that was me mother's brother. And then there were me Uncle Dick and me Uncle Joe and me Uncle Joe, oh he was grand were me Uncle Joe. Well I have a - his daughter's come h
ere yet. Me cousins you see. They come here and then - well I go and stay with them - live at - and live at Queensbury. And I go and stay with them but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Uncle Dick was the one that lived at Burnley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Burnley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And they used to come and stay with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you went and stayed with them sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you met at each others houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - I never remember - there were a few used to
 come to see daddy I remember from Chapel or - you know, a Mr Waterhouse and a Mr Crabtree and - and - and Mr Bladwin and I can remember they - but it'd be talking about the Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And they'd come and see your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they share any of the same friends, did they have any people they were both friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so, I never remember them having - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember your mother having and friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't, I don't reme
mber ever me mother having any pleasure much after her married, they just seemed to get married and - and they were there for that purpose you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, never had nobody come to our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you don't remember anyone being invited in to have a drink of tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A meal - no, no, no, not like they do today, no. No, they may have done but I don't remember it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that the people who called would call in casually with out an invitation
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 Just dropping in to see you, you know, just come - yes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't remember 'em going out, no. No they lived their own life didn't they in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What do you think your parents did when they did meet their friends, although you said they rarely did have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, no, I don't remember them having friends. We
 used - you see they're all the big families and you used to make your own amusement in the family. Well we used to all play games or something you know. I don't know what we used to do, I can't think what we used to do but I expect we passed the time on 
some way or other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But you don't remember there being a get together of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I'm telling you this while we were young see. I don't know what we used to do when we got a bit older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Many people divide societ
y into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another? You said there were some better class people when you were living at Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, but - yes, well we only used to
 wash for these 'ere better class. Just - you know do the bit of washing and then take it back and we used to get two spikes for taking the washing back. I remember it. They had a lot of money but never give it away. But that's all I can remember about th
at, can't remember much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How would you divide society up at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well, we used to live on our own, we were just the family you see and - and poor, used to bother with poor, and the better class'd bother with the better class, just - just bother with the people that were our class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You've already referred to your self as being poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What sort of people belonged to the poorer class, what sort of houses did they live in and what sort of jobs would they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well they were all doffers and spinners at - at the - works as twisters you know. Mill - we all - we all went to mill. All went to Haggas's Mill and - them were that we just bothered with when you went - when you went to the mill but - I - we
 never did bother with anybody better. No. We used to call 'em - all better - you know, they're all better class folk most of them didn't want to talk to us and all that sort of - I think it was also inferior complex you know a lot to do with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What sort of people were there better class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - I don't know. I - if they had tuppence more than me then we used to think that they were something. Which they do today, do today, yes, many a time say, oh well they think they're tuppence more than me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you thought of quite a lot of people as being better class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
There was a lot of 'em, yes, they all lived un these great big houses and we used to think we hadn't to look at them, never talk to 'em, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I don't know as ever we were brought up to it but we used to do it you know. Our - our own class would stick together you see, the poorer class. Yes, 'cos you'd think that you hadn't to have anything to do with the other class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember ever being told to curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Never - never did }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 curtsey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . We always had to show respect to elderly people. 
People that was older than us or people that was better, that we thought were - more money, not better but more money. More money than we had but - not to - acknowledge them so much as curtsey to them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember calling anyone sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Only - I'd call them Mrs, I do today. Call everybody Mrs and Miss. Today, but they don't a lot of them, use their names you know all the time. Now it's funny, I've a very great friend - a very great friend. They call her Mrs Cummins, and she said
 to me one day, let's call one another us names, and to call her Toby. And I said, yes, I'll try. And do you know in about two days after I said, I'll have to start calling you Mrs Cummins again, I cannot say it. I couldn't say it. No I couldn't, no. And 
m
y daughter said to me - she - this Mrs Cummins lived by my daughter and she said, it's 'cos they call you Esther mother and you don't like it. I never did like it you see, don't like me name. And she said, she says, you're thinking that Mrs Cummings'll ca
ll you Esther you see, and you don't like - I said, I don't care what you say, what you'll think about it, I said, I don't care, I'm not having it. Always call everybody Mrs and Mr.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways, calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, not a lot. No, not a lot. Saying - Mrs - they called us Cole you see before you were married, before I were married and I never remember a lot of people saying Mrs Cole. No I don't They would do I - well they called he
r Jemima but they wouldn't call her Jemima would they. Called me mother Jemima and me father Ely. So they wouldn't call them that but I - I can't remember it. They would do but I can't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 As Sunday school }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  did the children call your father sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I fancy they did but call Mr Cole I should say. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the village in Oakworth, who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I should say the schoolmasters and teachers and all that. Remember the lady that taught m
e, they called her Miss Hartley, and do you know she married Crabtree at Keighley that kept Riddlesden Hall - Louis Crabtree they called her I can remember that and I know where she lived up on - the top of - top of Lidgett Hill. She lived up there. I can
 remember that. And we used to look up to them, they were it you see, we used to think they were it. Yes. Schoolmasters and teachers, anybody that's in good position in the Sunday school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And they were the most important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Rather than the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - oh we had - the Haggas that lived at top of Brigg, mother used to wash for him, I used to - we used to go up and take the clothes back. And there was a lady that - that looked after him, I don't know what they called he
r, she were right mannish sort of a lady, I've forgotten a lot, and she - we didn't like her to take these clothes off us 'cos she didn't give us anything. But they called this man that she was housekeeper for, Mr Haggas, Haggas's at top of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And he was the woollen mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He belonged to the mill at the bottom where I worked, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would Haggas's be considered important in the village?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh very important, used to give to every - to people who went and said they were poor and all that they
'd give them something. Oh they were very important people were Haggas's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You told me Alistair Coling dying so you remember the time when he was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he also be considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was right good, yes. But y
ou couldn't get at him so much you know, there were always these servants and all that you see. You had to see them first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He sounds in a bigger way than Haggas's were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was in a bigger way. As he was called sir - Sir Isaac Holding. Not when we were there but he was after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 He owned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4211207  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 
mills in France didn't he?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know where he owned mills but he must have owned some mills somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So the mill owners and teachers were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Why were they considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They'd more money. Yes. More money than we had. Yes, it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 simply}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  there, they were that class of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not very much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you just came into contact with the teachers at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh the teachers would - yes, went to school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't come into contact with them outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never nothing to do with them. You finish at school you finish with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I'm just trying to establish who associated with whom at that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would you say the clergy were friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, they were very good - the clergy you see. But they'd only - they wouldn't bother with you any other time, only when you went to
 church or chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Outside of church who would you say were their friends, who would they call upon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I never - I never remember anybody - coming to our house much. Not clergy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, the shopkeepers - they'd be same you know. They had tuppence more than you, they'd think they was something. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You wouldn't say they'd be friends with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You wouldn't - no, you wouldn't - mix with them. You wouldn't mix with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would they mix with do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't know. Happen somebody that what went their own - thought they were anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would you say the teachers were friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know, happen their own class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you know any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It was surrounded by farms wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it was surrounded by farms but I - I can't remember. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about the employers such as Haggas's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Haggas's Mill.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who would they be friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No - I don't know, I never knew anything about them. Only they lived in a big house and you hadn't to hardly look at it you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I thought there might be gales in the village of who they did entertain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I don't know - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They kept themselves to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, they did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
What sort of people would you say went to the church and what sort of people went to the chapel, did you think there was a difference or were they similar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I can't remember who went to chapel when we did you see only one or two of these 'ere bigger men -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Would you say that both wealthy and poor went to the church and chapel or would you say that there was a difference between church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we used always say that there were a bit - you know - the clever type that went to church, always used to say this about }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 church}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
, see when I started going with Bobby and he went to the church I thought happen he were a little bit better than me you see. And we used to feel like that about the church, the Church of England. Not today, but I think we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you have some quite wealthy people who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, the chapel, yes there were. They kept the chapel going you know. Lot of wealthy people. But we was chapel k
eepers you see, we used to look after the chapel keep the chapel clean, the Sunday school clean. Remember going dusting with me father many and many a time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living 
or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, very different groups. Very different groups. There was still was people then that didn't do what we thought they ought to do you see, they'd go to - the pubs you know and al
l that sort of thing and - have different - they'd entertain different - different ideas of amusing theirself you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you think of a set of people or a family who would fit in this group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - no, I know - used to live - they didn't used
 to live - go to chapel, there were only daddy and - and I that - that went to Slack Lane, I don't know about the other chapels you see, I've forgotten now but - I know there was - there was one family and the lady was a Catholic and they lived a differen
t life altogether to what we did you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And they lived on Mill Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They weren't Irish were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - yes, they were, they were Irish people. We used to call them Irish, you know, Irish woman - a woman like but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How would you say their life differed from yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I should think the - they'd have beer in the house and - oh - I know they do today I know - everybody does here but they would you see, well we didn't. And we happen thought we were superior to 'em, 
I don't know. But we never did you know, we never did live like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you talked of entertaining, what did you mean by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well they'd happen have - men come in and women come in and happen have a drink you see, which isn't wrong, I'm not
 saying it's wrong. But happen they would do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would they drink to excess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well some of 'em did, yes, there were one family particularly called Sattersthwaites. They lived in Mill Lane. And they didn't live the life that we thought they ought 
to live you know. No, you know - remember your mothers and fathers used to say things about them, you know, that - well it's all - it shouldn't be shouldn't that you know, everybody should live their own life but - they didn't do and they don't do today d
o they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And there was this difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Yes. Happen - well happen - you know, go and have a drink - got to the pub and - well it's never been our life at all hasn't a pub life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were there children any different than you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well 
I don't - no - yes, us children. Well I don't know as they was any worse than what we were. Only were - you know, they're at home - of course they go to pub and all that, well it was wrong you see, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They would tell you not to play with those children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Not to go with them - play with Sattersthwaites because - that - you know, the fathers and mothers go to pub and all -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But were they very poor do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, they were all poor, yes, they were very poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think they would be poorer than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they couldn't be no poorer than we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember what their father did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't know what he did, no. Can't ever remember the father and mother, I can remember the daughters you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you would describe this family as being rough in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, we used to think they were rough but we used to think they were rougher - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7756763\charrsid4211207 rougher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  class of people than we were. Only because they did that, and it was all silly, it was wrong to - to think that in my idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So in the working class you would classify some people as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Also within the working class would you say there were some families who were thought of as being respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, some working classes would be, particularly respectable, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know - terrible lot of labourers where I was younger, terrible lot of labourers, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 There weren't any craftsmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, no. Well it used to be - coo they was something if they were craftsmen but the labourers, there were - there was a lot of them. Yes. There was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I should think they did. Yes, I should think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't - I don't - remember them - they went with anybody - they just seemed to plod along.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember them discussing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't remember the - the life. The life like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think it was possible at that time to move from one class to another, from perhaps the working class to the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so, not unless you won the pools. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we used to say so and so - oh, of the ladies you know - the ladies and you had to like eat humble pie to them, you know. If 
you did get to speak to them but you never got to speak to them hardly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Why do you think they would be called a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 'Cos they were tuppence more than you as I said before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It wasn't anything about the way they lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 No - well, they would live - they would kept theirself to theirself you see and then they'd have a bit more money than you, you see. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But they keep theirself to theirself so one certain class always did you know. They didn't mix.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh often used to have policemen walking about in the streets and then you don't have them now do you. Not so much. There is a policeman, lots of them I know and they do a good job of work but - they used to walk 
about ever such a lot and the - you know, I used to think that they always used to frighten you about a bobby, say, I'll tell you bobby of you, but I don't believe in that and I never have. I think a policeman ought to be your friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your mother would say this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she used to say, I'll }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 tell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  bobby of you. But, now I don't believe in that, I think a policeman is your friend. That's what I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How do you think the policeman treated people at that time, do you think he treated them as friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, no, I don't think they was as friendly, I think they were a bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 
vicious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  you know with the policeman in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Rented? Oh yes. Oh yes, had rented house. Used to rent 'em off Haggas's you see, nearly all
 Mill Lane - nearly all Mill Lane were Haggas's houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they used to have a rent man, called him a rent man, he used to come every week for the rent you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you think about the rent collector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
The rent collector? Oh he was all right, yes, he was - he'd be one of the men from the mill. Yes, and you would pay him and say, I can't pay this week. There used to be that sort sometimes, always give him a double - double on another week and
 there' be something crop up you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember what you thought of Mr Haggas as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't remember anything about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I do. Yes. I do. It was a struggle. All their life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you think about it at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I think all the pleasure that a woman got was living with this man. There was - the husband to her. And I think they h
ad to love one another and that was the pleasure that they got out of life. Now that's what I think about a lot of the older people. That that was the pleasure they got out of life, was loving one another and living with one another. I do. Not going out a
nd enjoying theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At that time when you were very small do you remember having any thoughts about the fact that they had to struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 Yes, I did, I used to think - but oh I thought, if only they could come back what a - how you would - oh 
I thought many a time how you would be different to people if you had your life to but you can't you see, you live one life and you're finished with it then and if you don't do then, that's what I tell lots of people - oh - I say lots - people that goes o
n the cemeteries puts flowers on the cemetery, it isn't mea, I keep flowers under my husband's photo there, every day, always, whatever it is, I keep some flowers there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
And there's - don't put them on the cemetery for everybody to see, not me see them. Well I - that's what I think about death you see. No. No. I don't think so. I don't think that you ought to do that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh it made a lot of difference. When they were 
out of you're your money were - it were just finished you see, there were no going to the dole. No, no signing on at the dole. When you had no money you hadn't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You told me that he was fairly frequently out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. He was many a time out of work. I can remember, you know, a bit about it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember whether you got any help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. No, I'm - we never did. I can always remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We had -
 we used to manage, yes, we never had that. But you could get it if you went and told them the tale you could get it, but we never did, I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When there was someone in the district who the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so. No. No, I - no, I - I can't speak -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You don't remember anyone being made to leave the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, I can never remember that, no, no I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh I don't know when I first went to school, I should think I'd be three or four happen. I don't remember going to small when I was very young, no, I don't - anything about that when I went to school when I was very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Which school did you go to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
To Oakworth board school. Top of - near by the by the Wesleyan chapel you know. Just a - well I don't think it's - is it there now, by Holdings, they chapel by Holdings Hall. A chapel. I think they pulled it down. Y
es. It's across the road and then just down Station Road a little bit and on there was Oakworth board school. But I went to church school first, to Oakworth church - the church school and I can remember me mother took me there and I can remember me father
 
coming and; fetching me away from there because he didn't believe in church. They were silly you know in them days. He didn't believe in church. I went to church school a little, yes, while. And then he took me away from there and went to board school. To
 board school, yes. I can remember the way we used to - to - to it. Past engine room belonging to Haggas's Mill and - used to watch these things going round like this
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you used to walk up Mill Lane and past that big engine room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And down Station Road to where this board school was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The board school was nothing to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207  do }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 with the chapel was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, it hadn't nothing to do with chapel, it was a board school. The other had a lot }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 o do with the church you see, t
he Church of England school. It was just by the - by the church, on - in front of Goodley is the church. You know where the church is. Well there used to be a school just by - it's there today. Well it belonged to the church well they used to learn you to
 say catechisms and all that you see well - my father didn't believe in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long did you stay there, a few days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I weren't long - I know I weren't so long at - at that school no. And then I had to go to the board school and I went to the
 board school 'til I were twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you spent most of your time at the board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you walked there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. We used to walk there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long did it take you to get to school, about five minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, it w
ere longer than that getting to the board school, it'd take us a quarter of an hour, yes. Oh yes. Take us a quarter - 'cos you know you generally stop and talk a bit don't you on the way and - and we walked - had clogs on, well, had clogs on. All cleaned,
 lovely clean clogs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you have your midday meal, did you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We used to come home, I never remember - they never made them at school. We'd come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you think of school at that time, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we did
n't - we wasn't - no. Because we weren't learnt to think about education you see. We weren't learned that at all you see, we learned all - all they wanted you to do was go to work try to bring a bit of money in you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And how did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh I liked Miss Harley, our teacher, I liked her. I don't remember anybody else. And I can remember one hymn that we used to sing, Arise - and - oh I can remember this 'ere }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 hymn}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  ever so well, we used to sing this specially - oh and I did like Miss Hartley, I can see her now, and she were a lovely person. Miss Hartley. I only remember her. But I liked her ever so well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality, ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I daresay they would do, yes, I - yes, I should say they would do, yes, I should say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You can't remember them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, can't remember those a lot about it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well you used to get caned a lot. Oh we always used to get caned. She didn't cane us but she used to send us to the headmaster but what his name ware I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the girls get the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh used - hold your hand out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember any offences that you'd be caned for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I don't think so, it'd be something perhaps that you hadn't done in your sums or something of that. I don't - perhaps there'd be something, I don't know. No, I don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your parents showing an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Not a lot. No. Not a lot of interest in your school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they ever ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I couldn't say, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember them ever visiting the school, meeting the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, never had no parents and teachers association. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't - I don't thinks so. I don't think they did. No, I can't remember a lot about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh yes, some, yes. Some that we used to - they used to sit - well one parson particularly I remember, and they called her Alice Aneaten, and s
he - they had just a little bit different bringing up and they was it you see, we used to say - we - you know, it was all silly was this, but we used to say they was it in school because they had that little bit of - of different bringing up than what we 
had you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And the teachers would help it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
And they would seem to help them more than the others. But I never remember whether she did pass her exam or not but she wouldn't try to pass happen to go to the mill because she wasn't - they wasn't 
that type of person you see. We had to try to pass to go to the mill - for to go full time to the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, there would be gangs, yes. Can't remember what they were, no, but there were - there we
re people - girls and boys that went about in - a lot together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Twelve when I left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you twelve when you went half time to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I were eleven when I went half time. I went a
t eleven. And twelve when I finished. Used to get up at five o'clock in the morning to go to work as we had to walk to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think you would have stayed any longer if you'd have had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I bet I should. I don't know wheth
er I would - then or not you see. But now I would if I could be - far from educated that we ought to be you know like in - it wasn't enough education wasn't just going to being in standard two. Wasn't enough education. But on the other hand you - you live
d with that class of people, they - they all went to work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't go to any part time education afterwards did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. Just went to mill and that were that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes I do, lots. I wish I was educated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You wish you'd gone on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I wish I was. Too late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I think we - well we wouldn't know how to read and write would we. Be like my mother, you see, we do kno
w how to read and write, I can write, I can - oh it's - only - style but still people can understand it. People can understand it. Well - that's - if you can read and write - but beyond that we didn't - didn't learn a lot, no, not beyond reading and writi
ng. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 While you were at school did you do any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When I was at school? No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were ten you went half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Eleven. Eleven. Half time at eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What were you doing half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I was a doffer.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was that for about twelve months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, 'til you got - well 'til I was twelve you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And when you were twelve you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Started and then I went - into spinning you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you work at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Hagga's at Oakworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You were still at Oakworth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we were still living at Oakworth then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you went doffing first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Doffing and then - fly - fly spinning they called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And still at Haggas's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, still at Haggas's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were working half time you worked mornings one week and afternoons the next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were doing this did you work Saturdays at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we all worked Saturdays, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 All day Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes - no, 'til one o'clock. Half a day Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How much did you get paid when you were doffing half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well we didn't get anything first week and then you starred with eighteen pence and - then a week or two - a bit after we got two and six you see, up to for and six, when we - when we was eleven - when we was twelve I should say. Up to four and six.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And when you started full time, how much did you get then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't know, I can't - I've forgot how much, I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 tried}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  to think I don't know how much we got. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But you were getting four and six already as half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Half time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And then you started full time, what were your hours full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we went at six o'clock in the morning and give over at eight 'til half past for breakfa
st, come home for breakfast. If you lived nearly by, or take it with you. We lived nearly by. And then - start at half past eight 'til half past twelve. And then half past twelve to one for dinner. And then half past - half past twelve to half past one I 
should say, an hour for dinner and then half past me to half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you continue to work Saturdays at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, oh yes, we worked Saturdays. Was a long - I don't know when it was but it was a long time that we worked Saturdays, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, never got no holidays with - no holidays with pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were working full time and part time, did you feel that it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, it did - I didn't think it - well - you know
 - money wasn't then what it is now you see, in - in - you just - it were just what everybody got and - really the employee hadn't the power over the em - the man - the man that run it like they have today. You see, they have power over them haven't they 
really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You mean you weren't in a union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, no. And still everybody - they were - they just managed you know, it was a matter of manage, there were no unions then. No. Oh no, were no unions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you got your wages, both part time and full time, did you give all the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, every ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did she do with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I don't know, she'd look after you that were all because there were - there were three younger than me that wasn't working when I
 was half time you see. Well you know they take some keeping don't they.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you started work how did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh ever so well, I always did, yes. I always did get - I do yet get on with people, I always have done, yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh we never saw him, we never saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who was immediately over you at the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - the - there was a man there called the overlooker you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well, treat you as - you as mugs at six of him you know what I mean. You were just there to do his bidding you know, always have been, the overlooker. You was just there to do his bidding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This applied still when you went full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. It always - they were always - they always had power over you had the overlookers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't know, I think it was just a matter that you had to do it you see, you know that it was t
here and you had to do it. Had to get this money from somewhere for your parents. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were doing half time as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 doffer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 , did the job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I think perhaps it did, yes, I don't think - education wasn't what 
it ought to have been you know. Education - It was - I don't think it was at all - I don't think it - it did help you at all going to work with your education, no. I think you'd just think oh the sooner I get away the better. Just to get the money you see
, what you was after - for your parents. I can't - I don't think that ever we bothered about education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You started work as a fly spinner when you were twelve, how long were you a fly spinner at Haggas's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Now you're asking me, I don't know. No, 
I don't know. I don't know when - when we came to Keighley. Can't remember in between. Can't remember in between that time no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You worked as a fly spinner for a number of years didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And then you moved to Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And then we came to Keighley, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you do when you moved to Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I went to - to work at Sugden Keighleys, we called it Dodie Keighleys, they were bottom on the main street. In Keighley. Sugden Keighleys, I went to work there and 
I was a spinner there a long time, but a cap spinner there. It was different you see and - in them days, I don't know whether there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you do that until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 Oh no, I were a weaver a long, long time. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I went - after I le
ft - after I come out of spinning, went into twisting, this were all at Sugden Keighleys, I went into twisting. And then I - I stayed there a while then I went in the weaving and I were a weaver - oh - nearly - you know, a long }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Until you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh yes, 'til I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You were married in 1911 so you must have been a weaver right up 'til then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I was. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 
Yes, I was a weaver a long, long - I'll tell you where I was a weaver at, at Low Holland, at Oakworth. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You know Low Holland? Don't you? In the main - Howarth, it's nearly in Howarth. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think it's Tin Lane way, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
It's - oh - I can go to it but you see I don't know what they call them. But I was a weaver a long while at Low Holland, when - I lived at 
Keighley then, I wasn't married and we used to go on the train, up - up to Oakworth. And a man called Charlie Grunty used to go, him and his wife. And I used to go with them, oh and they were ever so kind, they were, you know, when you've a man with how y
o
u think you - and we used to go pass a dam when we went. It were half way up Station Lane. Station Road and we used to go along - along a path, only narrow path, and past a dam and I used to be scared to death passing this dam. And at one time someone had
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 drowned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 theirself in that dam. But - we used to go in that - and then - I don't - I don't know where - what they call it, and we used to go along past this dam, along a bit and then down some steps and then past some houses and - and just round like that u
ntil Low Holland. Oh I worked there a lot - a lot of years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That would be quite long days for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh it was. Yes, well we used to - used to get a train - go on the train at Keighley. Oh and it were dark and miserable, you know, it was terrible
, the train, and these people used to get on at Ingrow. Used to get in my carriage. Then we used to get - there were no buses you see. Eeh I'm talking about such a long while ago, were no buses. And - we used to - I used to dread coming home at night, it 
was always so late you see when we got home at night. And, you know, having to come on the train, they - these people used to get off at Ingrow and I used to have to go back to Keighley. Well I - don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who owned the mill, was it still Haggas's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
I don't know who owned - no, I don't know, it wouldn't be Haggas's - I've forgotten who owned - it could have been Ackersley's, I've forgotten who owned - but I know ever so many people that worked with me you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 There was one young lady they called her Elsie Roach, she's died, just a - but it's - Eric Token\rquote s wife and he advertises in the paper selling suit lengths. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Well it was his wife. Elsie Roach. And she's - no, she didn't stand for us when we got married, but we had Elsie, my daughter, nin
e month and three weeks after we got married you see, understand don't you, nine month and three weeks after I got married and she - she was - she was god mother for her and that's how we called her Elsie you see we called her Elsie Roach, and she was a n
ice girl. Well she worked by me at Low Holland. We used to go to our house, at her - her mother's you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old were you when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Twenty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you must have worked at Sugden Keighleys for a few years and then you must hav
e moved back up to Oakworth to have worked for a few years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you worked there until you started to have your first baby did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, I didn't, I worked at Cloughs when I was - no, I didn't work there when I were married. But jus
t after, you see, I must have worked there a bit 'cos I must have known Elsie Rhodes from that. But this Elsie Rhodes, she used to come to my house ever so - you know, with her just being married, you know how you are, and you have these friends come in, 
a
nd she used to come ever such a lot. Well, as a matter of fact I didn't know I was having the baby you know how you are, we was quite Ignorant you know, I didn't know I was having the baby 'til I got a bit fatter you know and then I had to give over, but 
I worked at Cloughs when I were having the baby I know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At Robert Cloughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At Robert Cloughs at Ingrow because I lived at Ingrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you start working at Cloughs after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, before I was married, yes, before I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you were a weaver then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Because I know I got married from Marlborough street and - I got married from there and I used to meet daddy, he worked - he lived in Ellworth Road, just up here, he lodged just on this road that goes along 
here, he lodged here, I didn't know this place then, and I used to meet him at the top of Lawkholme and walk up with him, he worked at Alms and Pearsons, up Goldwin Street and I worked at - and we used to walk you know. Right from - Marlborough Street at 
Lawkholme right up to Cloughs in a morning, I used to meet him in a morning, walk with him to the bottom of Goldworth. You know, it's - it's been - had a hard life haven't we when you think of always had to walk you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know why you made these changes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - oh I don't know, why - why I did, I think we used to - well I went to - I went - I worked at Cloughs one time then I got daft. They wanted a motor driver at Cloughs and I - I went to see the man and I got daddy on there and he worked
 there for years and years there and we lived - we lived up there when we were - after we got married, did daddy and I. But I've forgotten rather a lot that happened in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Have you done any mobs since?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I've worked all me life. I've worked all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
I was - I was - daddy - daddy had a sister that had a girl that was just twenty-one when she died and she had never walked. And her was in rather a good position and I used to do
 all that - this - sister of his, I used to do all her cleaning, her washing and her baking and daddy had a garden across here and he used to do all the gardening for her. Do - get her all the potatoes and all that kind of - and I used to carry - and we l
i
ved in Cheltern and I used to carry them over to Showfield, the washing. And she used to bring the washing down every Sunday, they used to come here every Sunday for tea. Funny all this you know. She used to come, and her husband bring this little girl be
c
ause I had the girls you see, she used to come down and bring her - this little girl for tea every Sunday, and bring the washing down with her. Then I used to take it back the following Friday and through the week I'd do my baking you see and do a bit for
 her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 She sort of employed you to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, she did and I used to get three shillings a week. I did. And we thought it was good and she used to save it for me to pay me rates for this house. Saving three shilling a week 'cos - you see - oh - it's - I bought this house. Barry was at }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  war and she - she lived in this house, Barry's sister lived in this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . She was - her husband was starting in business on his own, he was a plasterer, Edwin Sowey they called him, and he went to - live - the
y - he thought he'd be more central and he went into Showfield, to live in Showfield. So when they were leaving this house I said - Berry was away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the 14-18 war that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I thought - he was away and I thought, I've a good mind to b
uy their house, I - had saved a bit of money cos he was - he had a position that he got a wage when he was in the Army, yes. He worked in the forest - in a - with the forestry of - sown in the New Forest and he got a wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your husband did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he was in the - Army goes like that see. He was - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the Flying Corps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. And - he was with these Australians and they worked in this forestry and he used to drive a lorry for them. And - and he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This was his job in the Army was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, in the Army, yes. He was a driver you see in the Army. And - well he was away and I wrote and asked him if it'd be right if I bought his sister's house, oh we used to spend all our spare time down here and we lived at Ingrow. We us
ed to spend our spare time here. And he said, yes, if I could manage it. And I did all the buying of this house. I did - I've lived - and we've lived here fifty-three year. Lived here ever since. Since - yes, and I did all the buying of it myself and he w
ent - he left me at Ingrow and he came back here. Came back after - after the war - the war was finished you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So during the first world war and probably just after you worked as a sort of helper to his sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. Yes, I did, yes, I did all her work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you do in the way of going out to work, have you been back in the woolen mills?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh - yes, when we were - lived at Ingrow - we settled at Ingrow. When we lived there I had the little girl, well after she got as she could t
oddle about the lady next door said she would look after her, she was an elderly lady, she would look after her. Do you know, and it were starting at six o'clock, I was in the weaving there and Barry used to carry into this house wrapped up in a blanket. 
N
ow they wouldn't do it today would they. To carry her into this house and put her in bed with this lady you see, and then she used to look after her for the days and I used to fetch her home at night. I used to go home for dinner and Barry used to get - B
arry used to get me me dinner at Cloughs canteen. He used to bring it home and keep it warm. We had a proper range you know. He used to put it on there and keep it warm for me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you kept working at Cloughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Until I was going to have Emmie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The second one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, 'til I was going to have Emmie. And then I finished and I didn't go to work in the mill no more. No. I worked for his sister you see. I didn't work for his sister when all this - when I was working at the mill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Have you done any jobs since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Haven't done anything, only - helped his sister you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You haven't been back into the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, I haven't been back into the mill, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You've just done jobs at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
 Brought the children up and done jobs here but - work - oh different houses, I used to go across there to B.D.A. There - there used to be a big house at the corner - there, that the B.D.A. and I forget what they called that - eeh now what they call that 
man - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was he the wonder of the Bradford Dyers Association?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, he had a right good job there, he must have had some money in it because he lived there and she was a right old lady and I went across there to help her so many half days but I
 wasn't going to this other place you see. And I went across there to help her, but he were a right drinker were that man and he used to come home drunk at night and take his clothes off and scatter his a money about, didn't care you know. She always used
 
to say to me - Harry used to say to this lady, I've found some more money under the bed - she would take it off, put it on - eeh Mrs Davies, you'll have another star in your crown for doing all this for me. Oh she was a grand old - she was ever such a nic
e old lady. Anyhow I - I don't know why I give over there. I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But you've always done little jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Always done work. Helping - yes, yes. Always have - I've always been cleaning you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just sort of part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Looking after the girls you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Do you think you would have preferred another type of occupation had you your time again, do you think you would do something else other than be a weaver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well happen to - well I'd have to learn typing or something of that or office work or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think you'd have preferred that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I don't think so. Always liked housework. 'Cos I'd been brought up with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 
us}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  you see. I've always liked housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you had your time again do you think you would do something other than be a weaver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so, I liked weaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you enjoy the company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we had some real good time you know. Got friendly with such a lot of people while I was weaving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never belonged to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, never had, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
When you were a weaver did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers? Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you feel that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, perhaps you did and, yes, I was in there weaving at cloughs and the menders, they just felt cut above you see, they used to - yes, they did, the menders there. And I know some of 'em now, I go to one lady's house, that was a mender when I was a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 weaver}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
. She isn't a cut above me now but she - thought so then. Yes, I did. I used to think they were, yes, I used to think that - that if they had a bit better job at all they were a cut above me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And mending was a good job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Mending always is - yes. Yes. Well - they - they always used to think theirself something that were menders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was that because it was an easier job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, yes, it wasn't - they wasn't as dirty, they didn't get dirty. You see, we - y
ou don't get dirty in weaving but we had to clean the looms in them days, we hadn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 meant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 to come and clean them like they have now. Men - boys or men come to clean them, we didn't have anybody to clean our looms. We had to do it ourselves and we used to get ever so dirty. And - so that'd be - that'd be why you see, that they }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 thought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  they was a bit - a bit better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you continue to live at home with your parents after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did starting full time work change your relationship you're your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, just the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I was always very happy at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you still go to chapel on Sunday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, after I got to know Derry I still went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 To Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Sunday school. Both my daughters were teachers at Sunday school. They aren't no
w you know, they won't be now but they did then. Ah they've got a different attitude to life but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Never. No. Derry never did too much and so I didn't you see, you know how you are with them don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time, in the evening and weekends, going walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you were a member of the Christian Endeavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Christian Endeavour, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, the Band of Hope and Christian -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way or did you do different things when you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we hadn't the Christian Endeavour - I went to the Christian Endeavour a fair bit but afte
r - but - after a while I think it fell through, you never hear - you haven't heard of the Christian Endeavour for a long time. It were just a religious meeting you know. But we still went to the Band of Hope, used to be the temperance hall to lantern lec
tures at - and that was kind of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you go out in the evenings once you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh yes, oh we used to go different walks, I - I had a friend and we used to go out Spring Gardens Lane and - oh walks, we - that was the way we used to spend our time you see. Walks in an evening or in Devonshire Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never joined anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, I never joined nothing, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you usually went with this friend of yours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. There were nothing to join in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you make any new friends once you'd started work, either boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh well I always had a - I had boyfriends, I - you know, just friends you know, yes. And girls but - not - had one or two they would call them mates you know in them days. One
 or two girls I had, different once, but not a lot. Never had a lot of different ones you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you come to met them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I think it was at the mill that I got to know this Anne Agrenen that I went with. I think it was at the mill and - then
 I went with another young woman, oh I've forgotten what they call her - yes, oh I've forgotten, can't just say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. Always bought friends home after - after, you - know after a while you know. At first - aft
er you get a bit bigger you see we used to bring friends home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - I don't - I know before - long before I were married I had - had girlfriends you know and we used to have boyfriends and br
ing 'em home but - they were only friends yes, we did used to have boyfriends and girlfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And where would you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh we used to go to the temperance hall. Temperance hall with these girls and boys. There were about four of us all 
used to go together. And - these boys used to - well we sat by them you know, but - we were all good friends you know, we used to temperance - oh I've never been anywhere only - happen to the temperance hall you know or - anywhere like that, you never wen
t -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would your parents meet all these friends of yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you went out in the evenings with your friends did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I expect we used to tell them you see, we're just going - going o
ut for a little while, you see, and we used to - we used to go ever such a lot of walk. Always go walks of an evening and - and Sunday - Sunday night and Saturday night we used to walk backwards and forwards on Skips Row, you know, just backward and forwa
rds and boys used to walk backwards and forwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 On Skipton Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 On Skipton Road, yes, but they don't now but we used to. Up Spring Gardens Lane and all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I did. I went in at ha
lf past eight. Me father - well after - when me father were alive we used to be at the bottom of the street seeking me. Oh we used to get into trouble. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Twenty-four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long had you known your husband then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Two years. Before I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you come to meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
I met him in the Gala field at Keighley Gala. Oh yes, I can remember it quite plainly yes. He was with some more boys see and I was with some more girls and, you kn
ow, you look at him and you sort of smile at him, then I - I just forget what they did but I know on the Sunday, we must have talked to him 'cos on Sunday, that was on the Saturday the gala and on the Sunday we went to - we met them you know. And then we 
just - went - went with 'em all the time after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So first you met as a group did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. There was a - yes, yes. Just go with 'em yes, finish with these girls altogether then just went - went with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 From Wel
lington in Shropshire. And he lived with his sister and she came here because she was a servant and then working in Shropshire there weren't - work - there's no works you see there and they had to leave home to go to - to be servants and she came to be a 
s
ervant somebody down Dalton Lane. And then she got married and she lived down at the end here, just on the end of this road and he lived here, number four Ellworth Road. And - and he lived there you see. And that were when I got to know him you see, he li
ved there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh - save up money. Did we? And what a struggle it was. You know, when we got married we only had twenty pounds. We thought - talked about getting married. 'Cos I was - I should never have
 got anywhere at home and he wasn't at home you see. 'Cos me mother were always poor and I would never have saved anything, only got sixpence a week then. And - he didn't have much wage 'cos he was a moulder's labourer. He was a plumber when he was down i
n
 Wellington but a man died that he was plumbing with and he wouldn't have it again off anybody - with anybody else, and came up here, and - he got to be a moulder's labourer and he hadn't a lot of money you see. And we started tailing about getting marrie
d
. Well, we'd have to have some money. I can remember we bought a horsehair suite. Oh - give five shillings each for them chairs and ten shilling for the couch. Horsehair - I - our Elsie said, I remember this today, my daughter, a suite for sale with prick
l
es on she used to always used to say this you see. Well after I was going to sell it you see. And then I got another then. But we had no money. We'd saved twenty pounds, well his sister up here said, if - if we get married she'd lend us twenty pounds and 
i
t was in war bonds, we said we'd pay her back in six months if she'd lend us - lend us another twenty pound. That was forty pound we had when we talked about getting married. And we - we - she had it back in six months. And that was what we had and we sta
rted with an old burnt carpet - it were battened you know. All the cheap - cheapest things, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You wouldn't have a father then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Me father, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother help you in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, she couldn't, no. She couldn't help me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never got like do today you know, no I never got engaged, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You just decided to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we just decided to get married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long was it between deciding to get married and getting married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well happen about three months you see, I don't know, happen about three months, I don't know just - but we never got engaged we just said, we'll get married and - we got a house and it were a four and ninepence a week this house that we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could you describe your wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - yes, I could, I know what I were married in. I got a - a blue - a rather light - I've always been blue, I like blue. Rather light blue serge costume, and a lady made it me, they called her Mis
s Schofield, you see, I can remember these little bits of things, and it had a square collar on and all fancy silk, a - a big square collar down there. And it made up after for Elsie. And - and that were - I got a lace }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 blouse at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - called it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 Stoddard\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  on S
kipton Road, lace blouse and blue costume. And - and I had a big hat, blue felt hat with all different colours - silk, different coloured - oh it was ever so nice - right across there like that you see, rather - I have a photo upstairs of it. And - and I 
know - we got married at St Mary's church in Dalton Lane. St Mary's church, it isn't there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That wasn't a Catholic church was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, no. Church of England. Yes. Church of England. Yes. And - and we had just one taxi and we had this taxi to c
hurch on the Saturday afternoon, and taxi to church. And then back home and there were just his brother that stood for us and a friend of mine, Miss Nicholson they called her. She went to Canada after. And - and then they went with us to tea then they wen
t
 home and we went to the theatre at night. Yes, we went to this house that we're going to live in and on the Monday morning I went to work. And Derry couldn't go because he'd upset his - finger or something. He - he'd tore it you see and he was going to t
he doctor's and he was at home for a few days after. Oh I can remember all these - oh they're lovely little time, he used to be at the back of the door waiting for me coming in. Oh - they're lovely times you know when you think about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, just got a few but not a lot you know, not many. I know me mother gave me a pair of blankets and I have some of 'em - two - have two of 'em but very thin, I put 'em over top of me electric blanket you see now. Very thin, that he gav
e me. Just a few but not many, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you just had these two guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh no, there was no more. No, we'd only them two, yes, there were only four of us that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your mother didn't come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, she - yes. She were there we went to 
mother's house you see. But she didn't have her tea with us, she had it after you know. She went in the kitchen. I don't know what she were doing but I can remember quite plainly there was just us four sat down for tea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At your mother's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, at my mother's. And then we went to the theatre after. And - everybody - we bought a piece of pork at Hoffman's, that - it's still Hoffman's you know, it's - we bought it there and we bought this bit of pork and we took it to the theatre with us. Wel
l the shops - the shops was open you see 'til half past nine and ten at night. Isn't it funny how little things you can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You bought this pork for your Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 For the Sunday dinner and I can remember at Sunday just - just before d
inner time there's some - one or two men, you know, you're - you're husband gets friends with men at the work and they came and knocked at door and Derry went to door and - come in, and they said can we borrow your meat 'til next week. I can remember them
 - it were just a bit of fun you see. They'd think we hadn't any but we had you know. Oh dear, it's funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you didn't have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No - went straight to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It was a rented house from Robert Cloughs was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. No, not Cloughs house. I don't know - it belonged to - somebody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It was near Robert Cloughs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, it was yes, very near.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Not long, about - I didn't have my first baby though and you see I was only married ni
ne months and three weeks when I married - when I had Elsie. And about six month in a lady that worked with me at works she said, there's a house to let in Mill - I never liked in this house as I got - went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where was this first house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh Wheat Street they called it. Do you, it was at Wheat Street. And - and it were four and nine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Those are back to back houses aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, it was a back to back house. I didn't like it, I didn't like it a bit, when - if Derry wasn't when I got 
home at night I used to sit on the step waiting for him to come - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 daren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 go in the house. You see, I think it was leaving a house where there was a lot of us and going to a house where there was nobody and I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 daren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  go in at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And so you got another house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
And we got another house up - on New Road Side and that were three and a penny a week. New Road Side. Right in front of the Co-op. Right in front of the Co-op - by - just below the White Horse. They aren't there now. Pulled down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they through houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Well, they weren't back to back but it was right up to a field at the back of the house. Yes, there wasn't a back door but the house was right up to a field at the back. Wasn't a back door. But it was three and a penny we
ek from the Co-op, that belonged to the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it a bigger house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, only I was among people and I liked but and nearly by this lady that had got me this house. And I - they had a shop you see and I felt really better being - I - I liked living there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you lived at New Road Side until you moved to this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. No, no, then we went to live in - in Oak Grove. That's }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 as}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  it - now me brother lives there now, number three Oak Grove, me brother lives in that house now. He com
e in after I came out. And we didn't live there long before this lady was removing, she had sister in this house, she were removing, she see, Derry were at the war then. And this lady was removing and I got - I got and bought this house from Smith Whitake
r they called him. And I were nearly the first on this row that bought this house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would that be about 1917?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It's fifty-three years ago. Fifty three years ago. I've lived here fifty-three year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You've lived here since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In February.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you bought this house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we bought it yes, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you buy it, did you get it on a mortgage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we got it - we bought - got it thorough, yes - what did I pay - we'd saved a bit 'cos Derry were getting a wage you see 
when he was in the Army and we'd always been savers you know, we saved up and I - I forgot how much we had to put down, mortgage, but see bought it through the building society. I think we borrowed about a hundred and ninety five pounds. Well it was only 
t
wo ninety-five was this house. And I could get a thousand - they'd get a lot more if - if I got - if I sold this house and I asked a thousand for it I should be highly satisfied with getting a thousand for it because I only give two ninety-five for it, mi
n
d you, I've lived in it, I've done - I've had it you know, but I should be highly satisfied if I got a thousand for it. But we - we bought it through Keighley Building Society and I still have a little bit of money that I have in Keighley Building Society
. Well, it isn't a Keighley Building Society now, it's the Provincial now, they've changed you see. But that's how we bought it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old was your husband when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He's two year - well about eighteen month older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So he'd be about twenty five or twenty-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just about eighteen month is - I'm in October and he's in February and it was a year and that little bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And your husband was an engineering moulder's labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was a plumbers apprentice before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that was right at the beginning, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did he do after he was a moulder's labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was a motor driver. A long - yes - a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And then when he came out of the Army?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he kept 
- he worked - went - got - I got him a job across at the B.D.A. - we used to do that - them sort of things in them days, I got him a job across at the B.D.A. and as a driver there quite a time. And then he went to work - a man came to how - the man that l
i
ved next door, he said they wanted driver for the Shell, he worked in Alice Street, and Shell then had just a little - little hut place in Alice Street, they didn't sell much petrol then you know. And this man next door said they wanted a driver for the S
hell and he came here - Derry wasn't right satisfied across at the B.D.A. AND HE came here and he - he got this job, he had to go in front of 'em and put so much down, I think it was about a five pound security you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was that for the lorry driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 For the Shell. Yes, you had to do in them - well, he had to do, yes. Yes. So he didn't pinch any petrol or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it a tanker he was driving for Shell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. No, carrying cans at first. Cans of petrol. Two gallons then cans then. Bu
t they only had a little but you see. And he run this hut himself. He hadn't nobody there. Yes. Yes. He run it. And he sold the petrol but there no - they didn't take it out in them days you see, the lorries used to go for it you know and they used to get
 it in - there weren't many about you know. Used to get it just in cans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So he used to go to some depot to collect these cans and then sold them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - Shell used to bring them to him. From another place, I don't know where it were at but they used to bring them to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And he sold them from this little hut?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And he delivered them on his lorry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, he hadn't a lorry in them days, not just at first. They did want a driver but they - he were driving after - in a 
little while you see. They'd send a lorry to do this job just at first and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So he was actually selling the petrol at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Selling these cans of petrol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did he do after that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Then in a while - I've forgot now - i
n a while they built a new place down in Swaites, the Shell did, and he went to look after that. And he - he run that for twenty-two years. A petrol place and he had two drivers and an apprentice besides. Worked for him but he did all the - the - paper wo
rk you see, and selling the cans, they were cans of petrol at first and then in a while the - they'd storage tanks you see, and they give over with the cans and - and started this storage work. He had quite a responsible job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He did that for twenty-two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Twenty-two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So that would take him up to about the forties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - yes, I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did he do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - I'm - I don't - I almost think I'm boring you with telling you all this thing. He worked at S
hell, well they closed this place down here, trying to save money, closed this place here and he had to go to Bradford to be an office man in Bradford. Well he wasn't very well, he had a - awful arthritis oh him you see, yes, hand he wasn't very well and 
h
e went to Bradford. Well, it was on Canal Road to - toward Bradford where he worked. And he had to - he couldn't get on the bus to come home, he used to take his dinner, he couldn't get on the bus go come home because there was all these 'ere boys coming 
from school and all that kind of thing and he had to ride on the - on the tram or a bus or whatever it was into Bradford to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633244\charrsid4211207 Chester}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  Street to get on a bus to come home 'cos he couldn't get on in the intermediate like you see. And it just got too much for hi
m. So he wrote - he wrote to Shell and told them that he would have to give up. It was too much for him, doing this - traveling you see. And - and he had to go very early in the morning to get a bus to go down there. It was all right, he could go down but
 he couldn't get home you see at teatime. And - and he left there and he went to work at the Co-op in the check office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would this be during the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh it was - yes, it would be after - after the war was over. After he had worked th
is twenty-two year for this Shell. And - and he went - well he didn't like that. He didn't like the humbug of the people that was over him, at the Co-op. And he went to the gas office. And he finished at the gas office. And he - he must have worked for th
e
 Gas Board three or four years. And - he liked it very much. But his leg got so bad - oh he went and had an operation. He had - Mr Broomhead, we went privately. It took all our money, we all had it carefully planned you know, to see this Mr - this Mr Broo
m
head, he was specialist you know. And - and he set his hip joint, he had to go into hospital and he were laid in a plaster from here right down, laid a board thing it was. Oh terrible. And I - that was the worst part about it. And - and then he went to wo
rk for the gas board and he was a - it's a great disadvantage, 'cos it was set here and he couldn't bend you see, he used to have to sit, it was straight here but they didn't put no hinges in like they do today you see, they put hinges in here now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It relieved the pain but it meant that he was stiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. And he - and this lady that works at the - at the gas place works there now. Her that did all this for me. She used to take him to the bus, he was so ill and she used to let him link up with her
 you know and get to the bus and I used to meet him for years, I used to meet him at the bus stop here and bring him home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And then he had to finish work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Then he had to give over also he said I shame going to work, to me, I shame, 'cos he said 
- he said, I can do the work, I can sit there and I can do anything. But he - was getting there and getting home. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old was he when he finished work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was sixty-six - he worked - he worked eighteen month after he was sixty-five, 
'cos he said he thought it would help me and he knew once he finished and he never went out hardly after. Only that he was - at the disabled, you see - I - - I helped to start that you see really, yes, I went right at the beginning of a - when they had a 
m
eeting right at the first and - anyway it used to - they used to come for him and put him in a car, you know, to carry him into the car to go to this - disabled meeting and it was ever such a nice meeting and we made such a lot of friends there but he had
 
to give over. And he laid in this corner here, I always think it was - about this one, I had one single bed. And the doctor said he couldn't go upstairs. Anyway he couldn't. I've all marks on my steps up there where he used to get on the - put his foot ro
und like - all the paint off the steps upstairs where he used to get on the steps and twizzle round to get a bit higher. And he had to give over in time. And he - slept in this corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before he had to finish work did he do any casual work or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, of a night. When he weren't - this is when he were well - he always used to mark the field out for the Keighlians, for the football field. Mark the field out and then at night they had dances and he used to go - not every week - happen on
ce a month, and he used to go and take the money at the door. And then look after the door, it was always twelve o'clock when he came home. And on the Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was it for the rugby league football?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, for the rugby, yes - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Lockholme}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  Lane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. No, not for - the - the Keighlians.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, the Keighlians had a - they had a - they have a club now. And I used to let 'em come up and change, I hadn't a bathroom then in my backroom, I've had that made since, it was 
a bedroom. And they used to come here 'cos there were no houses down there and they used to play down there and they used to come here and change and I used to wash their clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was he paid for doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. He didn't get paid. Just a - they
'd give him something - there were a Mr Miller, Tom Miller they call him, and it's - well we're a little bit better off with club now Jack, I'll give you a pound. And we thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So he got a pound a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not a week, no, jus
t occasionally. Occasionally. Not a week. And that were what he did, just looked after the - the football field after the dance - the dances you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The time you were working at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Gloughs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  before and after your little girls was born, how did your husband feel about you working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
He didn't like it. But I had it to do. To get - to give - to educate the girls. I couldn't have educated them 'cos couldn't have let them stay at school, they would have had to go to work when they were fourteen, leave school and go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This was when you were doing the cleaning jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. But I let them go on. You see - they - they were very clever, they took after daddy, he were - he were very clever were my husband, and they were very clever at school and - they passed - what did they call it then - well they did have to go for }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 matriculation}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 and - oh I forget what they call it. It was scholarship, yes, she did - Elsie - Emmie passed the scholarship. Our Emmie's proper go ahead you know, her that's the librar
ian. Now Elsie were like me, she was always shy and backward you see and Elsie didn't get through the oral, they used to have an oral - had a - some kind of an exam, I forget - I can't just - scholarship exam but then if they didn't get right through it t
h
ey had to have this oral. Well Emmie didn't have neither of them but Elsie had the oral and she - she didn't get through it. And so I sent here to a private school in Alice Street. Well, took all my money you see. Sending her to this private school. But I
 wasn't going to have her let down you see. And she went when she was sixteen in there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How do you think your husband felt about his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh he liked it. He liked it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That was when he was with Shell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When he was - oh yes, he did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your first child was born in 1912?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Elsie. In 1912, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And Emmie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In 1915. And I just know - I know all that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You just had the two girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Never had nothing else, no. Nothing else at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were the children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, both of them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you know what to expect in childbirth, had it been explained to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I didn't. We didn't know a thing about it. I didn't know a thing about when our Elsie were born. I didn't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't know what to expect all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I didn't know what to expect when I got married either. I didn't that. Was ignorant in them days. Didn't know what to expect at all and mothers never explained things to you. Didn't know what to expect wh
en I got married. A shock you know, you do have don't you. And then I was having the baby, well I never - you see I was always very irregular of course before I were married, and then when I got married and I wasn't like that well I didn't think anything 
about it until I started getting a bit fatter you see. Then I thought - eeh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So no one told you that this irregularity could be due to having a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Yes, nobody never telled us - no, I never knew anything about - you see, we n
ever used to talk about these things, they were all new to you. Oh yes, you had - it were all hush-hush in them days you know. It was done I daresay was this - the - they do nowadays but it wasn't talked about the same. Might be better for them but it's d
one a bit too much in my idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you get on having the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I had me mother, me mother came to stay with me for a fortnight. She only had one boy at home then and then this boy came with her to live with us and stayed with me for a fo
rtnight and we used to stay in bed ten days, I always had to stay in bed ten days when we had our baby. And I stayed in bed for the ten days, then I got up a day or two then mother went home you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she help deliver the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, she did everything, yes. I had the doctor with the first one because Elsie was a breach baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And the doctor helped you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, well - doctor Moffatt - Doctor Moffatt then. And do you know how much he charged me? Seven shillings. Yes. And then just
 came a time or two after 'cos he said as long as mother was there she was used to it you see. And then when I had Elsie - when I had Emmie, I didn't have the doctor at all. She was born before he came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your husband help when you were having the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. No, he didn't. Didn't know ought about it. Didn't do them days, the didn't come and sit with you and hold your hand. No fear.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you had ten days in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, with both babies, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But no medical help with the second?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Well the doctor - daddy went down and told the doctor I was in - daddy went down and told the doctor that she was born you see and oh well, he'd come in in a day or two and he came in later on see I was all right. Then he hadn't had to bother 
any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did your mother take over the running of the house while you were in bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Making all the - yes. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 slept}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't have a nurse then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, just mother, yes. Oh couldn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 afford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  a nurse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh breast fed were both of them. Both of them breast fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you enjoy feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I used to enjoy it, we used to sit in front of the fire and I had a little rocking chair and I used to feed them i
n - you know, breast feed them sitting in front of the fire. Oh yes, I loved them. And does today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, in getting - doing away with it. That was the biggest difficulty. Yes. No difficulties feeding, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you needed advice about the babies when they were small how did you ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well, we did used to go down to the clinic, right down at Victoria Park from Mill Road Side, up by New Road Side we lived there when I had the babies, and we used to go down to the clinic. Yes, there was a clinic then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did they do at the clinic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Ah they just used to tell you what to do, just advice you know. Yes. Have a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there a nurse there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, there was a nurse there and we jus
t used to have a cup a tea and give you advice. Didn't bother with the baby much then, in them days. Give you a bit of advice what do but I don't think I went - I can remember going just for a day - happen day out you see. Used to push the baby out in a p
ram, we had a - an old pram we bought for five shillings, no fancy pram. No money like they have today for a baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If either baby was asleep would you wake her for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. Wait 'til she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 woke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  up, yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If she cried before the normal time would you feed her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, used to feed them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would you do if she didn't seem hungry, would you encourage her to go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't suppose so. Just leave her 'til she wanted it you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How long would you let her go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh I don't - I - I never remember about any time. They used to go sleep and then you'd just put her in a cradle, I had a cradle. Just lay them in the cradle after they'd gone to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How old would she be when she first had solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh about six month. Yes, we used to mash a bit of potato up and a bit of - vegetable up in some gravy and give it to her with a spoon and always used to give 'em - pobs we called it. I - I have it yet many times, boiled milk yo
u know and poured on some bread and put some sugar. Oh I've given loads and loads of that, pobs we used to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 wean}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 About nine month. About nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So for about three months you were feeding her and she had solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Solid food, we didn't have to give 'em as much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you do it suddenly or gradually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh very gradually, yes, very gradually. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the baby seem to mind being weaned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think so, as long as they were getting full I don't suppose they minded that. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you think at the time that it did any harm to a baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, no, they didn't used to cry a lot you know but - you did - if you were working you'd have to let them cry wouldn't you for a while.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever punish your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11236142\charrsid4211207 baby}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  when she was naughty?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No I never did, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How much did your husband have to do with the children when they were babies under a year old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh he used to have a lot to do with them, he was very kind to the babies, yes, he used to - he used to bother with them ever such a lot.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he ever feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Feed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 With a spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, he would do at a mealtime, yes, if you were doing something else you see, he would - oh yes, he did many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he ever change their nappies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think he did much of the nappy changing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he play with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he did used to play with them after they got a bit bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he eve get them to sleep by rocking them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, he would, he'd rock them - we had a cradle you know. But I am - Iron rockers on, iron rockers and we had a string - I used to be having - pulling the string with me feet and rolling the - teacakes and that out. Then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You pulled the string to rock it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Yes, used to be a string on you see 'cos you could do something while you was rocking the baby. Oh yes, had plenty to do in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When they woke up during the night would he get up with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he'd get up occasionally, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he ever take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he would take them out, yes. In the prams, yes. Sunday mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Without you going?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you know what your husband earned at that time before 1919, did he tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I always did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How much of that would he give to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He gave me it all, always did, always give me his money, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you discuss with your husband how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he wa
s - yes, he had a lot to do with the housekeeping. Oh yes. Well you - you'd nobody else to discuss this - this with you know and you used to talk to them about it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You were living in this house longer than any other weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And this house had a large kitchen and a large living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A cellar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 An attic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. And two bedrooms. Well now I've one bedroom and one bathroom you see. And - but I had the attic like a proper bedro
om because my daughter comes from Birmingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At that time would it be just used for storing things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh the attic, yes, because the girls slept in the back room, both together you see, they slept in the back room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never had any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No I never had - never have had anybody living here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you wouldn't have any paid help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Oh no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You did your washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about the clothes for you and your husband and the children, talking about before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh we didn't have - yes, we didn't have a lot of clothes. We had the necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he clothes be made and mended by you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. not made, no, no. I did a lot of making up to I had to g
o to hospital when I was forty-three, had me womb took away. Well they call it some fancy now but I did have me womb took away at forty-three and up to then I made our girls' clothes. Yes, I made their clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before 1919 when they were little girls you'd make their dresses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I had a - a lady that used to make them for them, I have some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 photos}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  with it, nice dressed they had on, shantung dresses, it were a lot of shantung in them days. And this lady used to make a lot of their dresses and the
n I started doing them myself in my spare time. And - and then after I had to go to hospital Elsie started, she was sixteen and she started doing them and she made - she makes them yet. She does her own -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Up to 1919 you sometimes made them yourself and sometimes this lady made them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If you bought any clothes where would you buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh I didn't buy them hardly any, no, never remember where I bought them but we didn't buy them, they had to be made up something that you'd done with yourself you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When would they have something new, would it be just when the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 others}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  were worn out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, when necessary. When necessary. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about shoes, did you always have new shoes or secondhand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. In them da
ys, yes, we did have to - not when I was little but when they was little - oh yes, they had. And I don't know where I bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you repair them yourself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Derry used to repair shoes, he used to do loads of shoe repairing. Any amount of it. He used to repair - mine too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When your husband was in the Flying Corps, was it in 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
The first war, yes. I've forgotten but - he was in the Home Guard, he was a Sergeant in the Home Guard from Cloughs. He worked at Cloughs then you see. Was driving, motor driver. And - and we were - I don't know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before he went away would he help with the cleaning and cooking and washing and washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, he did, yes. We used to wash - we had a set pot - do you know - do you know what a set pot is, and fire underneath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Yes. We used to get up and put a fire under for me 'cos - we had no hot water you see, fair bit getting the water hot. Oh yes, he used to help me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The other houses before you moved here were rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he do any decorating or repairs or improvements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Yes, he did, he always did. He was always a do-it-yourself man. Used to do all the - the repairs - the paperhanging and all that sort of thing. Oh yes, he did a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before he went in the Flying Corps would he help with the dressing and undressing and bathing of the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, no, I don't think he did much of their dressing and undressing, I used to do a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And the bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And - 
no, I know he used to go to his sister ever such a lot while I bathed the children. 'Cos I - I used to bath the children, put them to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 bed and get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 bathed myself and then I used to tell him what time to come home. Oh. 'Cos we had a bath here in front of the 
fire you see. And I used to give him a key you see, he went to a house just up in Waterman Street and he used to go and play cards with two men that he worked with you know, and - Mr and Mrs Mason and their - her husband's brother and him used to play, ju
s
t play cards you know together. Not for money 'cos they hadn't any, none of them. And - and I used to - so on Thursday night he used to come back about nine you see. Well he had a key to come in and then the bath was in, I - I used to go to bed early, you
 were bathed - that was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  you see. And then he'd empty the water. That were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 bath night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he tell the children stories when they were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I daresay he did, yes. Tell them a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 home truths}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  as I call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would he take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, he would, used to take them out a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you ever able to get out without them, would he look after them at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We used to - the pictures started and we used to go to the pictures. I used
 to go one night and he'd stop in and mind them and - and he used to go to another night. Yes. We never went together, we - to the pictures. 'Cos we hadn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 babysitters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  then, we couldn't - think of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 babysitters,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 and he used to stop in and mind the babies while I - I'd go, happen with a friend you see to the pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In 1919 your eldest would only be seven wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would she have any little household tasks to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no. No, not when she was little, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Later she would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, she'd have to wash up and that kind of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What time would they be sent to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well they'd both go together you see, they always - always went out together, always pals my two girls. Well happen eightish you know. S
o we had a bit of time after they'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they put themselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 After a while, yes, after a while. They had the back room to theirselves you see and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you and your husband had the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you used to have a bath in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How often would you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Once a week. Yes, always at Thursday night. Thursday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh Sunday morning all clean clothes on. Clean clothes on the bed
 I mean, but we used to change them on the Thursday night when we got bathed. Always changed your vest you know and all that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you eat your meals, did you have them in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to - well we did have a table in here
 but only got - you thought you were getting with - as in the kitchen, but had a square table in here. And we used to have our meal on the square gable in here. - Carry them out of the - 'cos we hadn't the kitchen as nice in them days, you know, you were 
poor and you hadn't the things in the kitchen that you have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What sort of cooking equipment did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh just - the - well - oh we had a gas oven for as long as I can remember. Had a gas oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never had a fire range did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. Yes, after - when we lived at - at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Ingrow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 , New Road Side, we had a fire and there was a boiler at the side and we used to boil our clothes in there, in this boiler at the side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But at this house have you always had a gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we had a gas cooker when we came here, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were small when was breakfast eaten, what time would you have it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh at eight o'clock. Between eight and half past.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you be all there for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Derry used to com
e home, he just - go in the morning - when he worked across there but after he used to take his breakfast with him you see. Used to take their breakfast, have a flask you know, and take his - but always come home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh bit of jam and bread you know and bit of toast. No luxuries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you'd all be there for the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. And we used to get meat and - quite a lot of things at dinner times you know. One good dinner, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would you have at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I don't know, I've forgotten now what we had - what we used to have at teatime. A boiled egg happen - our Elsie'd tell. I used to have the - I used to have top off me dad's egg. Many a time I've heard -
 she'd say, oh I can remember when I used to have top off me dad's egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you have anything special on certain days such as Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, happen - yes, at the week - weekend, yes, we used to have a bit of something special you know. A tin of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 salmon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you have anything special at dinnertime on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh yes, we'd have a good dinner at Sunday, some - a roast of meat you see and some Yorkshire pudding, potatoes and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you have anything different for a Sunday breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not at the Sunday breakfast we didn't no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you make your own bread at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, baked - you always baking. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 
The other - up at Ingrow had a - a big oven in there, used to bake the bread in the oven. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 This side of the oven. Boiler at that side and oven at this side. Used to bake the bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever make your own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Oh I made - hundreds of pounds of jam and marmalade.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, used to make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 piccalilli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never - we never been that kind of - people, drinkers at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never made beer then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never made any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never used to make medicine, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we didn't do much bottling, used to bottle little bit but not much bottling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Your vegetables and fruit must have been all bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, they was all - bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never had anywhere to grow them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever keep any hens or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, Derry used to keep hens and rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we had allotment down at these houses here then and
 they were all gardens and he used to have an allotment over there. He kept beautiful rabbits. We had any amount of gloves made and sold a lot of gloves, I used to take 'em to get made certain places, Halifax. - And we used to sell these - you know, prope
r }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 rabbit skins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You said your father had some rabbits at the allotment?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, my husband. Yes. Rabbits and some hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He didn't grow anything at the allotment did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh he had - yes, he had a garden, he had an allotment. Across there where he had the rabbits, yes. He had a - a - a hut.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did he grow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, potatoes and a few raspberry canes and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Brussels}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  spouts. Oh we had an allotment across there, when he was working you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the period before 1919 how many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh well we had meat a time or two happen through the week, yes, I daresay. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 We'd have meat every dinnertime, some left- overs happen from the day or two before you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When that was done, yes, we'd have some more. Oh yes, w
e always lived all right, after I got married you see. We lived well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever have tinned meat at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, tinned meat for - for teatime, not for dinnertime. Sometimes you know, happen at the weekend we'd have a tin of meat or - o
r a tin of fish, a tin of salmon or - scotch eggs I used to make a lot, all that kind of thing. Used to make all sorts of - meat roll, I made a meat roll this last week. Making meat rolls and all sorts of - I always have made a lot of things myself. Pies 
and - oh all sorts of things I've made myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never knew anyone at that time who did any poaching did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you eat your rabbits that you kept?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we - over there - yes, we did - that we had over there. The
y were beautiful, they were like chicken you know, as white as anything. Were nice. Oh yes, we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go short of food so that your husband and children could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think - no, I don't think I was allowed to do that, no. I think we all used to have pretty much alike you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So your husband didn't need to have a larger helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, he didn't have much - happen a bit - a little bit more but nothing much, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were your two little girls allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, yes, we got away from that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they allowed to choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh they had to eat it, yes, I used to see that they eat it, whatever there was. They never were fussy girls at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you say to them if they did leave anything on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well you have to eat that after you see before you start. But I didn't used to make them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they have wait until things on the table, such as the salt were passed to them or could they ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, they could ask for it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. They could. If there was it. I used to make a pie or - or whatever it was and put it on
 the table and they could have it as long as there was any, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they expected hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. No. They weren't. Daddy never was like that. No he wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, not to the table, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did you all leave the table, did you have to wait until you'd all finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, no, when - at dinner time they hadn't no time you see, get up and go straight away back to work. 'Cos Elsie 
worked up the mechanics and she used to walk all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 through}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 the park here to dinner. I used to have it ready and she'd get up and go back through the park and the same as Emmie, she worked at the library, you know where the library is in Keighley. Well she di
d same but she didn't come at the same time as Elsie. Well she used to come through the park, she used to walk home you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But when they were at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 At school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she get to leave the table then when she was finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, I always let them go, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did all the family sit at the table, did you have your own places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, you always did, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And did you all sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't sit by the fire if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, we sat - sat at the table to a meal, yes. All together you know at the weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who served the meal, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I served it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you pit it in tureens or straight on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we used to try and put it in tureens happen at Sunday. And we eventually did. Otherwise straight from the pans onto the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were too young to feed themselves, did they have a high chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we had a high chair, yes, we had a high chair and we used - had a tray in front
 like we had when we was little and we used to put their meal on there and we used - had to try and get it theirself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before they could fed themselves who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we used give it - I used to give it them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When your children were young did you feel there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, I did, I always felt as though there was - you had to bring them up in the right way, I never let them go their own way, you would make them do what you thought was right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes we did. Yes. No, we never - never argued about it, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you discuss it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I don't think we did, I think we just brought them up and that was that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, was always Derry, I never used to worry about - I never have much bother with them, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Was your mother alive when your children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she was alive a long while. She were alive when we lived down here. A long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well she used to come down once a week you know, used to come on the bus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go and visit her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, she
 lived with my sister up in - at Knowle - up at Knowle. Up in Acre Street. She lived with my sister up there and - and I used to go up there to see her when she was ill - when she couldn't get down you know, I used to go because my sister and her husband,
 
he was - he wasn't like us really, well just - used to go to the pub you see and she used to go with him at Saturday night and I used to go and sit with me mother, me and Derry, used to sit with mother while she went out with her husband. Always used to g
o up at Saturday night. Take her some fruit and - you know, things that she didn't let her have, she wasn't - she wasn't very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ask her advice in bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. She - she'd nothing to say beyond, do as you like you 
see, she - no,; well she'll - she thought as we knew more than her really you see because they were very humble was mothers and fathers in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It wouldn't be that she thought that you and she had the same ideas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh no, it - no - she - she'd leave it - just leave it to you, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about your mother-in-law?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well she was down in Wellington in Shropshire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How often did you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I didn't see her, only about twice a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you go to Wellington to see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
I used to go once a year with Derry, just once a year, she used to come up here once a year to see her daughter and she stayed with this daughter along here and she used to come to us a day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did she ever give you any advice on bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. She were - more or a domineering kind then my mother was but I didn't see her much you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you never asked her advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never used to ask her, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought t
o do for your children, were you always affectionate, did you always show affection to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I always have been, yes. You know, they - they always like loving does children don't they, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And about safety, were you very concerned about their safety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, I think I was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you very particular about what foods they ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I thought they ought - ought - they eat like we did you see and I thought it - what I made I thought was all right you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you discipline them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, they was very good, yes, they had to do what we said. And we thought we did the right thing. We thought so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you tell me anything else you felt you ought to do for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't think that there was anything particular that I - I felt - they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 knew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 - they both were very understanding theirself and they moved in that circle of people that they got to know what had to be done and all that. They had lot of both girlfriends and boyfriends and they were all in tha
t class that they all did what they ought to do you know, they never did mix with other people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When they were small did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Wel
l I thought they ought to do what they ought - what they ought to do to parents you know. I always - and I think so yet you know - I think they ought to just respect you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they us
ed to have to wait a bit you know, wait a bit 'til somebody else had given over. And they didn't like it. Yes, but didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you bring them up to consider was important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I think - I thought a lot of importance in life
 was to go to chapel and - go - well they went to church. They both went to church, they were both teachers at - 'cos I changed over to church you see, and they both went church. I thought that was the most important, I think getting things instilled into
 
a child when they're little that's why I think they ought to go to chapel when they're little, Sunday - Sunday school when they're little. They never forget it, it's never forgot. If they won't go when you've power over them and make them go and then - wh
en you haven't power over them they don't forget these things. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you tell them they should hit back or not if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Well yes, we used to say to 'em, well you hit 'em, if they hit you, you hit them back.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, there was, there was a little girl, they called her Lily Frazer and I never liked our girls playing with her. She were a bit of a bully, you know, there generally is them isn
't there at school and I didn't like her very much and I used to say, don't play with her and she didn't go to school with her either you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It was just because she was a bully?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, yes, she was. Don't bother with her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well I used to say to 'em now you'll have to go to bed but I didn't put 'em to bed many a time but we used to give 'em something to go on with. Not hit them you know but always talked to them a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't give them a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, no, never smacked much, no, very rare. Either - either of them, either me or daddy either we never did. We used to talk to them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they ever actually put to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, our Emmie was. This young one, that Emmie, she were a little bad 'un }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 
when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
 she were little 'un. Our Elsie never was, she were always a good lass and she is yet but our Emmie were a bad 'un. A little terror were our Emmie. She wouldn't this sort of thing, wouldn't get 
in bath and wouldn't get out of bath, wouldn't - we - we used to go on tram, she wouldn't beg on tram, she wanted to get on herself and they don't give you time. All that - that's how she were bad I mean. She wasn't bad, only that way. She wanted to do it
 herself you see. But Elsie would get on and no more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I should think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Or did one of you play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, I don't think so. No I don't think so. No. We both were pretty severe with them as regards teaching them what to do you know 'cos we thought that they ought to - you know, just respect people and always call everybody Mrs and Mr 
and not use their names. I think that's that a lot of respect you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you went out for a short time between having the children the lady next door looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 You didn't like taking her in there because you had to take her in in a blanket early in the morning?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You didn't like doing this at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, but we had to do it because you wanted the money you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Some people think that children should be with the mother all the time, ot
hers think it is not necessary and does them good to be with other people quite a lot too, what did you think at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh I used to think they ought to be here. Yes, I always did - they had lots of friends, they've always bought friends here. Th
ey've never gone hardly to other people house, always bought girls here you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I'm thinking of the time when you had to leave Elsie with the lady next door.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How did you feel about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh well I didn't like it, no, her idea wasn't my idea of life you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You would have preferred her to have been with you all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But the money was necessary you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When your children had a birthday would if be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, yes, we used to make it a bit different. Always had birthday parties you see, lots of children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would they have anything different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we'd always make a right - you know, jellies and all that and custards and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And they'd have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, any friends in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and children on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. I - yes, we used to - well we do yet you know, leave all the parcels for Christmas morning. Never
 open a parcel before and never do now I don't. Never open a parcel for 'em - we always have done. Always had 'em when they were little, had a Christmas tree and - always - nice little things you see at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What would you do during the day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh we play games have a dinner, we didn't have turkeys like they do now at all, you know, happen it'd be piece of beef or - happen a chicken. Old hens we used to have, shilling a piece old hens we used to - but - not like they do today but still it was
 a - it were very nice, yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we didn't, no. Only a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 . We had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 gramophone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did any of you play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No no, neither the girls couldn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did any of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No they didn't sing either. We had choir you know and they'd sing with the choir but not on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever sing together at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we did, we many a time sing - and do today when our Emmie comes up. Oh - we have a lovely time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We always played games, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Inside and outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. In the house, not outside but in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you play at in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We used to play at all sorts of little ga
mes, I don't know what they were. Oh - having elusive and poking and giving blindfold and poking. Say who is it - who is it speaking and all that sort of thing. Silly - simple little games you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. Can understand that can't you, our Emmie worked at the Library. Loads of books.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But while they were still small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, yes, we always had plenty of books, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 children\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  books you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we always had a paper. Yes yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A daily or a weekly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 A daily paper. And we used to get a Sunday paper then, I don't get one now but we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get any magazines at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not often. No, not 
a lot of magazines. Emmie used to bring 'em from the Library and - at night and she used to take 'em back in the morning - magazines.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But when they were both very small, before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, when they -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you get any magazines then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were still small did you belong to the Library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I have - yes, oh no, not 'til Emmie went to the library, after she went. We got tickets for the library after she went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the period up 'til 1919 do you remember ever reading to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We always have read to them. Read out of the little story books you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever read aloud to each other, you and your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, now, we didn't, no, we used to read together of a evening you know but - no, not to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well he used to take 'em to his sisters you know, he had two sisters and he used to take them out to his sisters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you take them to your mother's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And when you went down to Wellington would you take them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. We took 'em to Wellington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You'd both take them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes. Both of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they ever taken shopping with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We used to go shopping with us too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You and your husband would go shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, we would always go at Saturday. Saturday treat - doing the shopping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well, yes, they always went with their dad, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just the three of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. While I was doing something you see, making a meal. Oh yes, they used to go with their dad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Can you remember Bank Holidays before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I can't remember. W
e used to go walks I know. Used to take them a walking up Newsholme Dene and all up Bellhouse Lane, you won't know these places. Do you? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 
Newsholme Dene and Bellhouse Lane, well that's right up - up New Road Side right at top across road is Bellhouse Lane b
ut not to go over to Cullingworth, to turn this way and go all round there, we used to go round ever such a lot, just for a little treat. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. When we had our holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 That would be a Bank Holiday, would you take a picnic with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. You'd take a picnic with you, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You never went to the seaside for a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Oh no, we didn't that, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well we did, we went to Blackpool after the girls got a bit bigger. But not at first, no 
not at first. No. No. We didn't, no, never went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know why you never had a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 'Cos we hadn't the money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But your husband had holidays off work did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, did have, but he - stay at home you see. But they only had
 - he'd only just have what - what they said, he wouldn't ask for any more you know, happen two days holiday or something like that. Didn't used to have above two days you know. Not at - no, in the holiday, no. Two days, you had to ask for it if you had a
ny more. And he never could afford to ask for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well we - I think we just used to go shopping at Saturday, I think that's all. We - before we lived down here - we used to come down - used to push the kids down in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 pram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - come to live down here, come down here and have hour tea here and then push the kids back. We used to walk them with the pram. Elsie had to walk and Emmie in the pram you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Could you tell me how you spent Sundays at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Well - going to church and going to chapel and going to church and that would be all. Go to Sunday school 'cos they were - you know, after they got a bit bigger, you know, used to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In the period up until the time Elsie was seven she went to Sunday school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you and the children put on different clothes on the Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we always had Sunday clothes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I do and I d
o yet. Wouldn't work at Sunday. Everything. Knitting always goes up, no, yet. Knitting goes up there and stops there and I wouldn't read the papers. I read books you know. Write letters Sunday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The children wouldn't be allowed to play out on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They weren't - no, they weren't, no. I don't - they do all sorts now but I'm nothing to do with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were they allowed to play games in the house on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, they didn't play no games hardly in the house, no. They had frien
ds and I expect they used to go to them you see. After they'd been to chapel - to church and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you all go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I used to go meet - Derry was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 men\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  - the - what they call it - the - oh I've forgotten - bro
therhood. The Brotherhood, he was the chairman of the Brotherhood and there were about thirty used to go all men and I used to go - that was up in town, at our parish church and we lived here then. The girls went to a - to the church to teach the both of 
them and I - they used to go together. I used to go up to meet Derry and walk home with him and we'd have our tea all together, then we'd go to back up to - walk back up to church again at night Yes, oh we did. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 By}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  the way, it was your entertainment and all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you go regularly even when they were quite small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh yes, then - yes, when they was little ones we went yes. Not when they were four but - they was little. You know, they used to - we used to go in the morning you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever belong to the choir at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. I didn't belong to a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did the church have a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I don't think so, I don't think the church did, no, I never went to anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you belong to any other clubs organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No. Only we used to - the Brotherhood used to - used to run a - a jumble sale you know and we used to - I helped - always used to - well we used to organise that and organise dances. The Brotherhood used to have - just to keep the Brother
hood going you see and we used to have ever such lovely dances and I used to do all the - the catering for it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And your children went to Sunday school when they were old enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did they go to any family services at the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh they'd go as we went you know, yes. They got right friendly with the curate and - oh they were all right, yes, they went - a lot.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you say grace at meals at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No we never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever have family prayers at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. We used to rely on them - doing themselves when they went to bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were your children taught to say prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we used to teach them to pray. Yes, we used to teach them. And when they were little we used to have them kneeling h
ere when they was right little ones. But after get a bit bigger they soon get away from that you see and - did you say your prayers last night? Yes mother, but - whether they did or not you don't know you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you and your husband taught them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not at all. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you not have any political views at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well Derry was always Conservative, you know, what they are, Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And did you share that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, and I was what he was. Oh yes. What he was I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you didn't have any particular views of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You followed him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, I did, always. I thought he - what he knew it was right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you remember your husband \{ILLEGIBLE\} before 1919?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't - he never joined he used to go and vote but he never joined in. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But he did vote in an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But - now in the town elections he used to go and count the votes. Yes, he used to go a time
 or two and counted - I don't know what they call it - he used to go and count the votes, and he's gone - but from work you see they used to allow him to go from work to put the names on then that's gone to vote - what do they call it - you know, that day
 that they go to vote, they give you your paper to vote with and - he - he done a lot of that and then gone at night and counted the votes but that's all that he's took part in. Never gone }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 
arguing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  and all that sort of thing with them or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you think your husband ever felt under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I didn't, we were always the one and he wouldn't - wouldn't have change from being a Conservative whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Were you and your husband ever members of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he ever take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Not at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you and your husband were not doing your work how did you spend your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well - I should 
say we just sat and talked or read and - we used to - I think he used to - he'd go to the pictures one night but I went when the girls got a bit bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And he had his rabbits as well and things didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. And he had a lot of out - interest
 with going over to the gardens you see and then the - he had a greenhouse too, I remember that now, he had a green house and grew all lovely flowers you know. Yes. He had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go out together in the evenings, you told me you took it in turns to go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we did, well after they got bigger, yes, we did go out many a time, yes. But not while they were small, never left them, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When did your husband get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh half past five he used to leave work. Get home by six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Oh nearly every night at home, yes. We never - had no outside interest, never went nowhere much at night. Only up to this Mr and Mrs Mason up in Walden Street, we used to go up -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
And if the girls, after they got a bit bigger, they'd have friends in well we said, we'll go up to Mr and Mrs Mason's and play at cards with 'em. Or we used to talk to them, you know, just talk. And - and leave there and then come b
ack an hour or so later you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did either of you ever go to any clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, never have been. No, no, not club people, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you belong to a sick club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, Derry was in - he were in the sick club what the - Ra
c - no, not Racobites, I was in the Racobites - National Deposit. He was in the National Deposit, that was a sick club, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did either of you take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Sport? No. No, not particular, no, he used to - he was - oh, he was a footballer, I've any amount of pictures of him playing football.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would that be rugby football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes - no - association. Yes, oh I've a lot of pictures of him playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did he ever do any cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. He never was a cyclist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, he weren't a great walker. We used to take the - we used to take the Brotherhood over to Gill Grange, I don't know whether you've heard of that or not, walking over to Gill Grange. Always at a holiday now he'd arrange this and I have photos,
 I've any amount of photos, I have photos with a whole crowd of people with Derry and I, you know, in the tent and all these younger ones all round us, but just as a holiday over to Gill - Gill Grange we were walking. They all came because I had girls and
 these 'ere boys used to come. Oh - I know why they used to come.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did either of you ever have a bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Never. Not that I know of, I never did. Don't suppose he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were very small were you able to go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Not when they were very small we didn't go, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But you'd go to the cinema taking it in turns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any hobbies at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never did, no I don't think so. He used to do a lot - oh - I knit n
ow - yes, well I've always been a knitter and he used to mend the shoes at night you know, his sister on here, she had three boys, and these 'ere boys used to bring their shoes to our house and stop here 'til he mended them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have any other interests outside the home at that time when the children were still small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, no I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever go out to enjoy yourself by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I never have been people that's gone - well I had enjoyment here you see and that's been enough for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And just the occasional visit to the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Just - oh yes, occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But you'd never go out by yourself other than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did anyone outside the home help you to look after the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, I always looked after them myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When you were confined to bed who helped you then, was it hour mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes, when I had the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did either of you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not - only his sister lived on - just on - on there, his sister, but we never bothered so much you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you see her very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we didn't see them very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where would you see her, here or there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh she'd come here, yes, she used to come here some
times you know. She had three boys and I had two girls well you've - there's plenty in your house - they hadn't all the gadgets that they have now for cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, we always had friends, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where did you see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Just see 'em, sometime we used to say come down for tea. On a Sunday you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you and your husband share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we always had the same, yes. The friends that we had all along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you and your husband have any friends of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, no, I know, say this were friend - I - I did have a lady up street that I used to go out with but she's died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would she come and visit you here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, and I used to see her 'cos here husband were away and my hu
sband were - here husband were at work and my husband were at work and I used go see her. But she's died you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you ever actually invite friends into your home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - now and again, not very often. Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you offer them things to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. We used to make a tea you know, come along to tea you see, and then stay 'til the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would this happen on a particular day or occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh, on Sundays, yes, on Sundays, never through the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you say that the friends invited in were friends you shared or particular friends of your husband or you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, not - not of Derry's, no, nor of mine, no, we shared, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did friends call in causally without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, not often. No, never have been one of them. Never have been like that that anybody can just - no, no, I never have. Only the girls' friends used to come you know, they used to come at night and sit and knit and - you know, they always did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 When the children were small did you ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Not unless Derry went, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 And you'd take the children with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, that's take them with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 People often tell us that in t
hese days before 1919 people made their own amusements, what did you do when you got together with your friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We'd just sit and talk, yes, sit and talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You wouldn't have any music or games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. No, happen - I know I've he
ard girls say many a time, it never were talk that we could join in, we always - you know - just talked - small talk. It's only small talk. It is nowadays if you meet anybody and they come to see you, it's only small talk. It's nothing serious you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You bought this house yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. Bought it in 19 - when our Elsie was five. Our Elsie was five when I bought this house, when we came to live here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before you came here you'd lived in a rented house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 We lived in two after we were married - three I should say. Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you think about the landlord of those three houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - well I don't know - I just can't - one belonged to the Co-op and one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, we just used to tak
e the money at the co-op, the other belonged to Cloughs and they - they used to take it out of Derry's wage, we lived in Clough houses. And the other one I don't know how - when I got married I don't know what happened there. And I - I expect the land - t
he rent man would come you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you don't remember having any particular feelings about the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Oh no, no. No, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 In this district where you lived then who were considered the most important people would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 You mean in the - came to the house you mean or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 The people who lived in the district, who would you say that the people looked up to as being important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I don't know as regards round here, they're all on about like yourself you see, in a place -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 It's a working class area isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes, it is, they're all about like yourself and you're friends with everybody. There isn't a person - now at that time nor this that I don't speak to nor ever have done you see. Always been friendly
 you know with everybody. No, I don't know as there's anybody that I looked up to, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Who did the shopkeeper associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes. Oh very - very friendly with the shopkeeper. The boy that owns the bakery shop up there. Oh I'm very friendly w
ith him. And his sister used to go friends with our girls you see and - oh yes, I'm very friendly with him now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would the shopkeepers be friendly with the people who lived around them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes. They had to be in these little shops you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What about the clergy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Yes. Used to come, yes, Mr Cole, while Derry was laid here, he used to come every week. Used to come and give him communion and I used to have communion with him. Once a month came to give him communion but other times he used to come as a friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 But during the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh - no, I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Would you know who the clergy associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I should think that in the war that they would - they would be friends with everybody in the war wouldn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Do you know who the teachers were friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 There aren't any farmers around here are there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Fa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 rmers? No. No, no farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 How about the employers, say Robert Cloughs, do you know who they would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No I don't. Don't know those sort of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What sort of people would you say at that time went to the church and which sort went to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, they - they reckoned to be a little bit better that went to the - we used 
to say so then. And generally all Tories, it's funny. Never hardly come across a Labour man that went to church. Never hardly a Labour person that went to church. It was funny. They was classes. These went to chapel. They were classes as Tories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Where would you say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Liberals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207  went to then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't know where the Liberals would go, I don't like to ask into that. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 They were nearly all Conservatives that went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Yes, they were, they were class - happen not in later life - late life, yes, at that time was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
When you came to live here in this house did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living around here or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 I don't think there were different groups, I think they were all pretty much alike. Yes, I think they are today too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Did you have a struggle to make ends meet at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Oh yes, we always have. Yes, just after -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 What did you think about it at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Well I - oh of cours
e you were taken on with your man you know, you thought it were wonderful and all that sort of thing and every little thing you did you thought you're doing it for the home you know, and for your own interests you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11690153\charrsid4211207 Oh yes we were very poor because Derry only had a pound a week for a long, long time, 'til he went to work for the Shell and then he got a bit more and the Shell were very, very good to us. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 To - well they was to everybody you see that worked for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 Before he went in the Army and when he went in the Army, was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
Not much, no he never went - but he never were a union man and he never were brought out like a lot of 'em. He never was union man, no, we never had any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 He was never out of work for health reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 
No, well - he did - he did suffer bad health rather a lot but he wasn't at home much When he - when he worked for the Shell they used to give him his wages if he were off work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4926748 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 So you never had to get help from the Guardians or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6685924 ED  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16064692\charrsid4211207 No. Never. No, no, never. No.
\par }}